WEBVTT

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:12.500
The next part of our program will be an analysis of what tools we have to stimulate labor,

00:00:12.500 --> 00:00:18.500
and there are not so many of them, and what combinations can be made of this, and what we get as a result.

00:00:18.500 --> 00:00:26.500
So, let's take a closer look at the tools that we, as managers, have in stock

00:00:26.500 --> 00:00:32.500
in order to form a compensation plan that is attractive to our employees.

00:00:32.500 --> 00:00:42.500
A compensation plan is a house of cubes that our employee should like.

00:00:42.500 --> 00:00:51.500
Our employees are different, so we will provide different compensation plans to different employees,

00:00:51.500 --> 00:00:58.500
in order to stimulate their behavior, which is required of these employees for our company.

00:00:58.500 --> 00:01:04.500
But there are relatively few cubes from which these plans are made.

00:01:04.500 --> 00:01:12.500
Let's start with the fact that all these components of the compensation plan, all these cubes, can be divided into two categories.

00:01:12.500 --> 00:01:18.500
The first category is direct payments, that is, this is the money that our employees receive

00:01:18.500 --> 00:01:26.500
as compensation for working at our enterprise, giving us their time, energy, strength, knowledge, and so on.

00:01:26.500 --> 00:01:31.500
The second category is what is commonly called a social package.

00:01:31.500 --> 00:01:38.500
At first glance, the social package is not very related to stimulating labor.

00:01:38.500 --> 00:01:49.500
As a rule, it is not money, it is either a guarantee, or a compensation, or goods and services that the enterprise provides to its employees.

00:01:49.500 --> 00:01:58.500
Nevertheless, if we look at the most advanced and developed organizations, they have a large and rather complex social package.

00:01:58.500 --> 00:02:05.500
Let's take a separate look at the components of the social package and try to understand why it is needed and how to design it.

00:02:06.500 --> 00:02:08.500
Let's start with direct payments.

00:02:08.500 --> 00:02:12.500
Direct payments are also divided into two parts.

00:02:12.500 --> 00:02:22.500
The first part is the permanent part, that is, what our employee receives every month, regardless of how he worked.

00:02:22.500 --> 00:02:28.500
The second part is the variable part, which is the part that the employee receives to a greater or lesser extent,

00:02:28.500 --> 00:02:34.500
in connection with a particular collective or individual result.

00:02:34.500 --> 00:02:36.500
Let's start with the permanent part.

00:02:36.500 --> 00:02:42.500
At most enterprises, there is a thing called a positional package.

00:02:42.500 --> 00:02:50.500
To do this, a tariff grid is developed, that is, a table that shows which category of employees is subject to which package.

00:02:50.500 --> 00:03:01.500
As a rule, the tariff grid and its categories have a certain width, which is called a conditional fork.

00:03:01.500 --> 00:03:09.500
That is, within each category there is a minimum, a median, an average and a maximum part.

00:03:09.500 --> 00:03:13.500
We will look at how the tariff grid is formed separately.

00:03:13.500 --> 00:03:16.500
The second part is personal add-ons.

00:03:16.500 --> 00:03:26.500
In the case when a given employee does not pay the tariff grid according to his merits and values for the organization,

00:03:26.500 --> 00:03:31.500
we can offer him additional monetary rewards.

00:03:31.500 --> 00:03:35.500
For what? For the experience of working in our company.

00:03:35.500 --> 00:03:44.500
There are companies that add money to the old employees for remaining loyal to the enterprise.

00:03:44.500 --> 00:03:49.500
The more employees remain at the enterprise, the more these add-ons.

00:03:49.500 --> 00:03:52.500
Maybe for special knowledge and qualifications.

00:03:52.500 --> 00:03:58.500
Let's imagine that our organization actively works with representatives of different countries,

00:03:58.500 --> 00:04:03.500
and we need managers who can communicate in Chinese, Japanese, Hindi, etc.

00:04:03.500 --> 00:04:08.500
We can pay people for mastering rare foreign languages.

00:04:08.500 --> 00:04:11.500
I will say only one thing about add-ons.

00:04:11.500 --> 00:04:19.500
This is a very useful thing, because it individualizes the attitude of the employer to the employee.

00:04:19.500 --> 00:04:25.500
It shows the employee his personal, individual value for the organization.

00:04:25.500 --> 00:04:29.500
But I do not recommend getting too involved in add-ons,

00:04:29.500 --> 00:04:34.500
because it often turns out that all the order in the labor payment,

00:04:34.500 --> 00:04:40.500
which we tried to establish with the help of the tariff grid and the construction of premium rewards,

00:04:40.500 --> 00:04:44.500
is interrupted by a huge number of add-ons, which are purely individual,

00:04:44.500 --> 00:04:49.500
and as a result, the whole system loses its controllability, clarity and integrity.

00:04:49.500 --> 00:04:54.500
And finally, the constant part is the compensation for the worker's expenses.

00:04:54.500 --> 00:04:56.500
What is it?

00:04:56.500 --> 00:05:02.500
Imagine that we have several drivers on our personal cars.

00:05:02.500 --> 00:05:08.500
Of course, they spend money on the service, on technical inspection, on repair, on gasoline.

00:05:08.500 --> 00:05:17.500
These are the personal funds that a person, due to his position and role, invests in the work of our enterprise.

00:05:17.500 --> 00:05:22.500
Naturally, it would be fair if the enterprise compensated him for this money.

00:05:22.500 --> 00:05:24.500
The variable part.

00:05:24.500 --> 00:05:32.500
The variable part includes two components, one of which is called premiums, and the other is called bonuses.

00:05:32.500 --> 00:05:34.500
These terms are often confused.

00:05:34.500 --> 00:05:37.500
I propose to define them this way.

00:05:37.500 --> 00:05:43.500
The premium is what is relatively small in relation to the deposit,

00:05:43.500 --> 00:05:48.500
well, the maximum is 100%, no more than the deposit.

00:05:48.500 --> 00:05:52.500
And it is paid often, at a certain period of time.

00:05:52.500 --> 00:05:57.500
It is paid either once a month or once a quarter.

00:05:57.500 --> 00:05:59.500
What are bonuses?

00:05:59.500 --> 00:06:08.500
A bonus is a reward that is paid rarely, usually once a year, and it is large in relation to the deposit.

00:06:08.500 --> 00:06:12.500
For example, it can reach 10, 12 deposits.

00:06:12.500 --> 00:06:20.500
Bonuses are a significant expense for an enterprise due to their size.

00:06:20.500 --> 00:06:25.500
Therefore, it is not always advisable to pay them to all categories of workers.

00:06:26.500 --> 00:06:29.500
This system is not always effective.

00:06:29.500 --> 00:06:34.500
What categories of workers should be paid to, and why, we will find out in the third part of the course,

00:06:34.500 --> 00:06:38.500
when we will consider specific situations and cases.

00:06:38.500 --> 00:06:44.500
These are all the cubes from which we can draw up compensation plans.

00:06:44.500 --> 00:06:48.500
It seems that there are not so many of them, and the picture is quite simple.

00:06:48.500 --> 00:06:50.500
But this is only at first glance.

00:06:50.500 --> 00:06:55.500
Now we will consider these components of the compensation plan separately.

00:06:55.500 --> 00:07:00.500
We will try to understand the logic by which they are built, how they work,

00:07:00.500 --> 00:07:04.500
and what we need to do to make them all work effectively at our enterprise.

00:07:04.500 --> 00:07:11.500
Each of the components of the compensation plan has its own purpose in the incentive system.

00:07:12.500 --> 00:07:20.500
Let's consider them separately and try to understand what we want to achieve from the worker

00:07:20.500 --> 00:07:26.500
using each of these cubes or bricks that we have just discussed.

00:07:26.500 --> 00:07:29.500
The first one.

00:07:29.500 --> 00:07:34.500
The permanent part of the compensation plan, that is, the duty deposit,

00:07:34.500 --> 00:07:40.500
is aimed at providing the level of life that the worker would like to maintain.

00:07:40.500 --> 00:07:47.500
We remember that this is one of the most important factors in the worker's attitude to the incentive system.

00:07:47.500 --> 00:07:48.500
The second one.

00:07:48.500 --> 00:07:51.500
The permanent part provides the worker with loyalty,

00:07:51.500 --> 00:07:54.500
because he knows that he will receive it tomorrow and the day after tomorrow,

00:07:54.500 --> 00:07:59.500
and in the future, he will be given a promotion under good conditions.

00:07:59.500 --> 00:08:10.500
This is a feeling of confidence in the future and loyalty to our employee at the enterprise.

00:08:10.500 --> 00:08:18.500
And finally, the permanent part, due to its size, is our message to the worker,

00:08:18.500 --> 00:08:24.500
our signal to him that we highly appreciate his work.

00:08:24.500 --> 00:08:28.500
The high permanent part, high duty deposits,

00:08:28.500 --> 00:08:33.500
is a demonstration from the employer that the worker is appreciated by the organization.

00:08:33.500 --> 00:08:38.500
Again, we see a mix of moral and material factors of the incentive system.

00:08:38.500 --> 00:08:39.500
The variable part.

00:08:39.500 --> 00:08:43.500
As we have already seen, the variable part includes two components,

00:08:43.500 --> 00:08:45.500
that is, bonuses and bonuses.

00:08:45.500 --> 00:08:50.500
The bonuses are primarily the incentives for short-term results.

00:08:50.500 --> 00:08:52.500
What do I mean by short-term?

00:08:52.500 --> 00:08:55.500
Since they are paid out quite often,

00:08:55.500 --> 00:08:58.500
this is a signal to the worker that he has done a good job.

00:08:58.500 --> 00:09:00.500
But not only that.

00:09:00.500 --> 00:09:02.500
If the worker has done a bad job,

00:09:02.500 --> 00:09:03.500
violated the rules,

00:09:03.500 --> 00:09:06.500
did not bring the results we expected from him,

00:09:06.500 --> 00:09:09.500
then we can reduce this bonus.

00:09:09.500 --> 00:09:13.500
And in this case, if we talk in the format of a wick and a gingerbread,

00:09:13.500 --> 00:09:17.500
then the bonus is not only a gingerbread,

00:09:17.500 --> 00:09:20.500
but also the possibility of using a wick, if you want.

00:09:20.500 --> 00:09:25.500
That is, if there is a high premium component in the compensation plan,

00:09:25.500 --> 00:09:29.500
it can be used as a punishment for the worker.

00:09:29.500 --> 00:09:31.500
That is, to deprive him.

00:09:31.500 --> 00:09:32.500
Bonuses.

00:09:32.500 --> 00:09:36.500
Bonuses provide several factors at once.

00:09:36.500 --> 00:09:40.500
First of all, it is a guarantee of loyalty,

00:09:40.500 --> 00:09:42.500
a guarantee of prospects,

00:09:42.500 --> 00:09:46.500
because if a person knows that at the end of the year he will receive a large amount,

00:09:46.500 --> 00:09:49.500
then, accordingly, he will probably work this year

00:09:49.500 --> 00:09:51.500
and will not leave us.

00:09:51.500 --> 00:09:54.500
The second is the stimulation of long-term results,

00:09:54.500 --> 00:09:55.500
unlike the premium.

00:09:55.500 --> 00:09:58.500
There are a number of positions, especially top ones,

00:09:58.500 --> 00:10:03.500
where it is impossible to achieve results within a month or a quarter.

00:10:03.500 --> 00:10:06.500
The results are visible only at the level of the company as a whole,

00:10:06.500 --> 00:10:08.500
in the long term.

00:10:08.500 --> 00:10:13.500
And, accordingly, bonuses support this work for the long term.

00:10:13.500 --> 00:10:16.500
And finally, bonuses play the role of moral support,

00:10:16.500 --> 00:10:18.500
of course, very strong,

00:10:18.500 --> 00:10:21.500
because it is a very powerful signal to organizations and workers

00:10:21.500 --> 00:10:23.500
that they are valuable to them.

00:10:23.500 --> 00:10:26.500
I know organizations where workers say,

00:10:26.500 --> 00:10:28.500
well, our salary is not very high,

00:10:28.500 --> 00:10:32.500
but we work mainly for bonuses.

00:10:32.500 --> 00:10:35.500
And finally, the social package.

00:10:35.500 --> 00:10:38.500
The social package solves several problems at once.

00:10:38.500 --> 00:10:42.500
First, it contributes to the level of support

00:10:42.500 --> 00:10:46.500
of the level of life of the workers to which they are oriented.

00:10:47.500 --> 00:10:50.500
Second, it provides loyalty.

00:10:50.500 --> 00:10:53.500
And, on the other hand, it demonstrates to workers

00:10:53.500 --> 00:10:55.500
that the organization is promising

00:10:55.500 --> 00:10:57.500
and is going to work further,

00:10:57.500 --> 00:10:59.500
and will not leave the market,

00:10:59.500 --> 00:11:01.500
and will not be kicked out of work.

00:11:01.500 --> 00:11:03.500
If the organization invests in the social package,

00:11:03.500 --> 00:11:06.500
it demonstrates its stability.

00:11:07.500 --> 00:11:11.500
Of course, the social package plays a significant moral role,

00:11:12.500 --> 00:11:15.500
because it demonstrates the employer's work,

00:11:15.500 --> 00:11:17.500
the care for its employees.

00:11:19.500 --> 00:11:21.500
How does this happen?

00:11:21.500 --> 00:11:23.500
We will see a little later.

00:11:23.500 --> 00:11:25.500
Now I will say only one thing.

00:11:25.500 --> 00:11:29.500
An effective system of stimulation of labor

00:11:29.500 --> 00:11:33.500
requires us to design our house,

00:11:33.500 --> 00:11:36.500
or a set of houses of different compensation plans,

00:11:36.500 --> 00:11:39.500
depending on what we are, first of all,

00:11:39.500 --> 00:11:42.500
and what categories of workers we expect.

00:11:42.500 --> 00:11:45.500
Providing them with the right standard of living,

00:11:45.500 --> 00:11:48.500
prospects, attachment to our organization,

00:11:48.500 --> 00:11:51.500
stimulating short-term results,

00:11:51.500 --> 00:11:54.500
or stimulating long-term results,

00:11:54.500 --> 00:11:56.500
and moral factors,

00:11:56.500 --> 00:11:58.500
that is, demonstrations to our workers,

00:11:58.500 --> 00:12:01.500
our mutual loyalty to them.

00:12:02.500 --> 00:12:05.500
There are several standard,

00:12:05.500 --> 00:12:07.500
widely known around the world,

00:12:07.500 --> 00:12:10.500
traditional compensation plans,

00:12:10.500 --> 00:12:13.500
which I would like to start with.

00:12:15.500 --> 00:12:18.500
The first thing to say in this regard is the question

00:12:18.500 --> 00:12:21.500
of what we will put as the basis

00:12:21.500 --> 00:12:24.500
of what we are going to pay the worker.

00:12:24.500 --> 00:12:26.500
There are two approaches.

00:12:26.500 --> 00:12:29.500
We will pay one worker their result.

00:12:30.500 --> 00:12:34.500
If it is a machine that produces parts,

00:12:34.500 --> 00:12:38.500
we want to pay him for a certain amount of parts,

00:12:38.500 --> 00:12:42.500
produced in a certain amount of time and without defects.

00:12:42.500 --> 00:12:44.500
If it is a sales manager,

00:12:44.500 --> 00:12:47.500
we want to pay him for how many clients he attracted,

00:12:47.500 --> 00:12:49.500
how much goods he let go,

00:12:49.500 --> 00:12:52.500
what amount, what is his turnover,

00:12:52.500 --> 00:12:54.500
that is, we pay according to the results.

00:12:55.500 --> 00:12:58.500
The second payment system is temporary.

00:12:58.500 --> 00:13:00.500
This means that we pay the worker

00:13:00.500 --> 00:13:02.500
for the time spent at work,

00:13:02.500 --> 00:13:05.500
provided that he was not just sitting on a chair,

00:13:05.500 --> 00:13:07.500
but was doing something.

00:13:08.500 --> 00:13:11.500
There are also mixed forms of labor payment,

00:13:11.500 --> 00:13:14.500
which we will talk about in more detail.

00:13:14.500 --> 00:13:17.500
I want to say right away that we can pay

00:13:17.500 --> 00:13:19.500
each worker separately,

00:13:19.500 --> 00:13:21.500
according to his results or his time,

00:13:21.500 --> 00:13:24.500
or we can use collective or brigade forms

00:13:24.500 --> 00:13:26.500
of labor payment,

00:13:26.500 --> 00:13:30.500
when the result, time, or labor of the worker is paid,

00:13:30.500 --> 00:13:34.500
and within it there is already a distribution of payment

00:13:34.500 --> 00:13:36.500
among the workers.

00:13:36.500 --> 00:13:39.500
So let's start with the payment according to the results.

00:13:39.500 --> 00:13:41.500
It is called a collective payment,

00:13:41.500 --> 00:13:44.500
and there are quite a few options.

00:13:44.500 --> 00:13:47.500
The first is called a simple collective payment,

00:13:47.500 --> 00:13:49.500
and in Russian it is called

00:13:49.500 --> 00:13:51.500
as you dig, so you dig.

00:13:51.500 --> 00:13:55.500
This means that if I stand by the conveyor

00:13:55.500 --> 00:13:58.500
and collect the devices,

00:13:58.500 --> 00:14:01.500
then from each device I have collected

00:14:01.500 --> 00:14:04.500
and left my workplace further along the conveyor,

00:14:04.500 --> 00:14:07.500
I get a certain amount of money.

00:14:07.500 --> 00:14:09.500
How much is calculated separately

00:14:09.500 --> 00:14:12.500
depends on the complexity of the work I do,

00:14:12.500 --> 00:14:14.500
the cost of this device,

00:14:14.500 --> 00:14:17.500
the risks, and a number of factors.

00:14:17.500 --> 00:14:19.500
Strictly speaking, this is a case

00:14:19.500 --> 00:14:22.500
when I do not have a permanent part of the labor payment,

00:14:22.500 --> 00:14:24.500
but there is how much I have done,

00:14:24.500 --> 00:14:27.500
or the same can be said about sales managers,

00:14:27.500 --> 00:14:30.500
we know that the system is quite widespread

00:14:30.500 --> 00:14:33.500
when a person does not receive anything from the organization

00:14:33.500 --> 00:14:35.500
except a percentage of sales,

00:14:35.500 --> 00:14:37.500
expressed in some units.

00:14:37.500 --> 00:14:40.500
It seems that a simple collective payment

00:14:40.500 --> 00:14:43.500
is simple, obvious, and very transparent.

00:14:43.500 --> 00:14:46.500
In fact, it has a number of disadvantages,

00:14:46.500 --> 00:14:49.500
starting with the fact that it does not provide

00:14:49.500 --> 00:14:52.500
social protection for the worker,

00:14:52.500 --> 00:14:55.500
it does not provide workers with confidence

00:14:55.500 --> 00:14:57.500
in the future,

00:14:57.500 --> 00:15:00.500
it does not show a positive attitude

00:15:00.500 --> 00:15:03.500
to the worker from the enterprise,

00:15:03.500 --> 00:15:05.500
and besides, between us,

00:15:05.500 --> 00:15:08.500
a simple collective payment allows

00:15:08.500 --> 00:15:11.500
a number of underground, under the carpet options

00:15:11.500 --> 00:15:13.500
how it can be managed.

00:15:13.500 --> 00:15:16.500
For example, the valuation of the same work

00:15:16.500 --> 00:15:18.500
can be raised or reduced.

00:15:18.500 --> 00:15:21.500
For example, a foreman who determines

00:15:21.500 --> 00:15:23.500
how many workers did,

00:15:23.500 --> 00:15:26.500
can only describe a small number of workers.

00:15:26.500 --> 00:15:29.500
In short, it is not so simple,

00:15:29.500 --> 00:15:31.500
not so beautiful,

00:15:31.500 --> 00:15:33.500
not so transparent.

00:15:33.500 --> 00:15:36.500
Therefore, for the vast majority of enterprises,

00:15:36.500 --> 00:15:38.500
including sales,

00:15:38.500 --> 00:15:41.500
today they refuse this simple collective payment.

00:15:41.500 --> 00:15:44.500
I must add one more major drawback

00:15:44.500 --> 00:15:46.500
of the collective payment.

00:15:46.500 --> 00:15:48.500
As soon as the worker is offered

00:15:48.500 --> 00:15:50.500
other valuations in another place,

00:15:50.500 --> 00:15:52.500
he also goes there with pleasure.

00:15:52.500 --> 00:15:55.500
There is a collective premium form of payment.

00:15:55.500 --> 00:15:58.500
This is when, in addition to the payment

00:15:58.500 --> 00:16:00.500
for the output or the results,

00:16:00.500 --> 00:16:02.500
bonuses are added for quality,

00:16:02.500 --> 00:16:04.500
for speed,

00:16:04.500 --> 00:16:06.500
for what we agreed with the worker.

00:16:06.500 --> 00:16:09.500
This is a more progressive form of labor payment,

00:16:09.500 --> 00:16:11.500
because it really performs

00:16:11.500 --> 00:16:14.500
a stimulating function for the worker.

00:16:14.500 --> 00:16:17.500
There is also a collective progressive form

00:16:17.500 --> 00:16:19.500
of labor payment.

00:16:19.500 --> 00:16:20.500
What is it?

00:16:20.500 --> 00:16:22.500
This form is used in cases

00:16:22.500 --> 00:16:24.500
when we need to complete the work

00:16:24.500 --> 00:16:26.500
as quickly as possible.

00:16:26.500 --> 00:16:28.500
We have an urgent order,

00:16:28.500 --> 00:16:31.500
and we need our workers to come out

00:16:31.500 --> 00:16:34.500
in time, for which we will pay them separately,

00:16:34.500 --> 00:16:36.500
and to cope with the production

00:16:36.500 --> 00:16:39.500
of the above-mentioned product as quickly as possible.

00:16:39.500 --> 00:16:41.500
Or, let's assume that we have a warehouse

00:16:41.500 --> 00:16:44.500
full of goods that need to be liquidated urgently.

00:16:44.500 --> 00:16:47.500
We can, of course, reduce the cost of goods,

00:16:47.500 --> 00:16:50.500
but this is not always profitable.

00:16:50.500 --> 00:16:52.500
Maybe it is more profitable for us

00:16:52.500 --> 00:16:54.500
to pay our sellers

00:16:54.500 --> 00:16:56.500
to work more intensively

00:16:56.500 --> 00:16:58.500
and to invest in the specified period.

00:16:58.500 --> 00:17:00.500
In this case, there is a collective

00:17:00.500 --> 00:17:02.500
progressive form of labor payment,

00:17:02.500 --> 00:17:04.500
which means that my workers

00:17:04.500 --> 00:17:06.500
get a big bonus if they cope

00:17:06.500 --> 00:17:08.500
with the work within the period

00:17:08.500 --> 00:17:10.500
we gave them.

00:17:10.500 --> 00:17:12.500
The next form of collective payment

00:17:12.500 --> 00:17:14.500
is accord payment.

00:17:14.500 --> 00:17:16.500
What is accord?

00:17:16.500 --> 00:17:18.500
It is when the payment is made

00:17:18.500 --> 00:17:21.500
not based on the number of produced parts,

00:17:21.500 --> 00:17:23.500
not on the number of sold goods,

00:17:23.500 --> 00:17:25.500
but on the performance of a certain,

00:17:25.500 --> 00:17:27.500
usually large, amount of work.

00:17:27.500 --> 00:17:29.500
In this context, accord payment

00:17:29.500 --> 00:17:31.500
is often used in a brigade

00:17:31.500 --> 00:17:33.500
or collective form,

00:17:33.500 --> 00:17:36.500
when a team, a team or a team,

00:17:36.500 --> 00:17:38.500
takes on the performance

00:17:38.500 --> 00:17:40.500
of a certain amount of work,

00:17:40.500 --> 00:17:42.500
and as a result,

00:17:42.500 --> 00:17:44.500
they receive the amount of money

00:17:44.500 --> 00:17:47.500
they agreed to pay to the employer.

00:17:47.500 --> 00:17:49.500
The simplest examples are

00:17:49.500 --> 00:17:51.500
when you hire a brigade

00:17:51.500 --> 00:17:53.500
to build a cottage.

00:17:53.500 --> 00:17:55.500
As a result of this work,

00:17:55.500 --> 00:17:58.500
you have to pay a certain amount of money

00:17:58.500 --> 00:18:00.500
to the building.

00:18:00.500 --> 00:18:02.500
It seems that this accord system

00:18:02.500 --> 00:18:04.500
is old and primitive,

00:18:04.500 --> 00:18:06.500
and it is mainly related

00:18:06.500 --> 00:18:08.500
to relatively simple types of labor.

00:18:08.500 --> 00:18:10.500
No, it is not.

00:18:10.500 --> 00:18:12.500
The same system is used

00:18:12.500 --> 00:18:15.500
in the payment of project management.

00:18:15.500 --> 00:18:17.500
When a project is implemented,

00:18:17.500 --> 00:18:19.500
no matter in what field,

00:18:19.500 --> 00:18:21.500
in the field of implementation,

00:18:21.500 --> 00:18:23.500
in the field of development,

00:18:23.500 --> 00:18:25.500
in the field of IT,

00:18:25.500 --> 00:18:27.500
in the field of design,

00:18:27.500 --> 00:18:29.500
a temporary team is created,

00:18:29.500 --> 00:18:31.500
a team, as they say,

00:18:31.500 --> 00:18:33.500
and this team works

00:18:33.500 --> 00:18:35.500
until the result is achieved,

00:18:35.500 --> 00:18:37.500
according to which

00:18:37.500 --> 00:18:39.500
this accord payment is received.

00:18:40.500 --> 00:18:42.500
There is also a well-known

00:18:42.500 --> 00:18:44.500
accord-premium system.

00:18:44.500 --> 00:18:46.500
This is when we not only agree

00:18:46.500 --> 00:18:48.500
to perform a certain amount of work,

00:18:48.500 --> 00:18:50.500
but also guarantee a higher premium

00:18:50.500 --> 00:18:52.500
if, as in the case of a

00:18:52.500 --> 00:18:54.500
production-progressive system,

00:18:54.500 --> 00:18:56.500
the work is done on time,

00:18:56.500 --> 00:18:58.500
a short period of time,

00:18:58.500 --> 00:19:00.500
as a rule,

00:19:00.500 --> 00:19:02.500
and with high quality.

00:19:02.500 --> 00:19:04.500
Temporary payment.

00:19:04.500 --> 00:19:06.500
At first glance,

00:19:06.500 --> 00:19:08.500
it seems more primitive,

00:19:09.500 --> 00:19:11.500
less stimulating than

00:19:11.500 --> 00:19:13.500
the actual payment.

00:19:13.500 --> 00:19:15.500
But let's look at the

00:19:15.500 --> 00:19:17.500
members of our employees,

00:19:17.500 --> 00:19:19.500
their role and functions.

00:19:19.500 --> 00:19:21.500
We have employees who

00:19:21.500 --> 00:19:23.500
clearly give a specific result,

00:19:23.500 --> 00:19:25.500
which can be calculated in rubles

00:19:25.500 --> 00:19:27.500
or in other units.

00:19:27.500 --> 00:19:29.500
And there are employees whose

00:19:29.500 --> 00:19:31.500
task is to ensure the process.

00:19:31.500 --> 00:19:33.500
The most striking

00:19:33.500 --> 00:19:35.500
manifestation is accounting.

00:19:35.500 --> 00:19:37.500
They do not give results

00:19:37.500 --> 00:19:39.500
but must perform their functions

00:19:39.500 --> 00:19:41.500
accurately and on time.

00:19:41.500 --> 00:19:43.500
Or, in the structure of your HR

00:19:43.500 --> 00:19:45.500
management, there is a recruiter,

00:19:45.500 --> 00:19:47.500
whose mission is to hire

00:19:47.500 --> 00:19:49.500
employees and fill vacancies.

00:19:49.500 --> 00:19:51.500
We can calculate how many

00:19:51.500 --> 00:19:53.500
employees he hired and what

00:19:53.500 --> 00:19:55.500
terms they served.

00:19:55.500 --> 00:19:57.500
And next to him or in the next

00:19:57.500 --> 00:19:59.500
room sits an inspector on duty,

00:19:59.500 --> 00:20:01.500
whose task is to provide

00:20:01.500 --> 00:20:03.500
the documents on time.

00:20:03.500 --> 00:20:05.500
So, temporary payment

00:20:05.500 --> 00:20:07.500
is used for those categories

00:20:07.500 --> 00:20:09.500
of employees for which it is

00:20:09.500 --> 00:20:11.500
impossible or difficult to

00:20:11.500 --> 00:20:13.500
calculate specific results.

00:20:13.500 --> 00:20:15.500
But it exists as a simple

00:20:15.500 --> 00:20:17.500
temporariness.

00:20:17.500 --> 00:20:19.500
The most primitive case is

00:20:19.500 --> 00:20:21.500
when we pay the employee

00:20:21.500 --> 00:20:23.500
the same amount of hours

00:20:23.500 --> 00:20:25.500
they have worked,

00:20:25.500 --> 00:20:27.500
in accordance with the tariff grid.

00:20:27.500 --> 00:20:29.500
It is clear that this form

00:20:29.500 --> 00:20:31.500
does not stimulate the work too much,

00:20:31.500 --> 00:20:33.500
so there is a temporary payment

00:20:33.500 --> 00:20:35.500
form, when in addition to

00:20:35.500 --> 00:20:37.500
payment for a certain amount

00:20:37.500 --> 00:20:39.500
of hours worked, the employee

00:20:39.500 --> 00:20:41.500
receives a bonus for quality,

00:20:41.500 --> 00:20:43.500
which can be reduced if

00:20:43.500 --> 00:20:45.500
this quality does not meet

00:20:45.500 --> 00:20:47.500
our requirements, or if

00:20:47.500 --> 00:20:49.500
the employee commits some

00:20:49.500 --> 00:20:51.500
violations of the discipline.

00:20:51.500 --> 00:20:53.500
Let's talk a little bit about

00:20:53.500 --> 00:20:55.500
collective or brigand forms

00:20:55.500 --> 00:20:57.500
of labor payment.

00:20:57.500 --> 00:20:59.500
We have already said that

00:20:59.500 --> 00:21:01.500
the accordant and accordant-premium

00:21:01.500 --> 00:21:03.500
systems are collective,

00:21:03.500 --> 00:21:05.500
because quite rarely one person

00:21:05.500 --> 00:21:07.500
can do a large amount of work.

00:21:07.500 --> 00:21:09.500
As a rule, it is a collective work.

00:21:09.500 --> 00:21:11.500
In terms of collective forms

00:21:11.500 --> 00:21:13.500
of labor payment, I want to

00:21:13.500 --> 00:21:15.500
touch on two points.

00:21:15.500 --> 00:21:17.500
As we said, we have employees

00:21:17.500 --> 00:21:19.500
who must give us the result,

00:21:19.500 --> 00:21:21.500
and we pay for the result.

00:21:21.500 --> 00:21:23.500
There are employees who must

00:21:23.500 --> 00:21:25.500
perform their functions, and we

00:21:25.500 --> 00:21:27.500
pay for their performance at a certain time.

00:21:27.500 --> 00:21:29.500
And there are employees whose mission

00:21:29.500 --> 00:21:31.500
is to organize the work of others.

00:21:31.500 --> 00:21:33.500
These are managers, these are managers.

00:21:33.500 --> 00:21:35.500
So we have to pay them for what?

00:21:35.500 --> 00:21:37.500
That's right, we have already

00:21:37.500 --> 00:21:39.500
mentioned this, for the collective result.

00:21:39.500 --> 00:21:41.500
How is labor payment distributed

00:21:41.500 --> 00:21:43.500
within the collective?

00:21:43.500 --> 00:21:45.500
We have agreed

00:21:45.500 --> 00:21:47.500
that for a certain

00:21:47.500 --> 00:21:49.500
time, let's say a month,

00:21:49.500 --> 00:21:51.500
we will implement a project

00:21:51.500 --> 00:21:53.500
for our employer.

00:21:53.500 --> 00:21:55.500
Let it be a consulting project

00:21:55.500 --> 00:21:57.500
for the implementation

00:21:57.500 --> 00:21:59.500
of our employer's

00:21:59.500 --> 00:22:01.500
effective labor payment system.

00:22:01.500 --> 00:22:03.500
Agreed? Great.

00:22:03.500 --> 00:22:05.500
And we have completed this work,

00:22:05.500 --> 00:22:07.500
and who of us should receive

00:22:07.500 --> 00:22:09.500
how much for it?

00:22:09.500 --> 00:22:11.500
There is a thing called

00:22:11.500 --> 00:22:13.500
the labor participation coefficient.

00:22:13.500 --> 00:22:15.500
This is a coefficient

00:22:15.500 --> 00:22:17.500
that is assigned to each

00:22:17.500 --> 00:22:19.500
of the members of our

00:22:19.500 --> 00:22:21.500
respected labor collective

00:22:21.500 --> 00:22:23.500
at the very beginning

00:22:23.500 --> 00:22:25.500
of the work or at the end of the work,

00:22:25.500 --> 00:22:27.500
and the rate of this worker

00:22:27.500 --> 00:22:29.500
increases or decreases

00:22:29.500 --> 00:22:31.500
according to how much he did,

00:22:31.500 --> 00:22:33.500
how much he invested,

00:22:33.500 --> 00:22:35.500
how much he worked there,

00:22:35.500 --> 00:22:37.500
what was his role,

00:22:37.500 --> 00:22:39.500
what was his mission.

00:22:39.500 --> 00:22:41.500
The labor participation coefficient

00:22:41.500 --> 00:22:43.500
can be assigned in a very different way.

00:22:43.500 --> 00:22:45.500
In some cases, it is initially

00:22:45.500 --> 00:22:47.500
negotiated in the contracts

00:22:47.500 --> 00:22:49.500
with the members of our collective,

00:22:49.500 --> 00:22:51.500
in other cases, as I said,

00:22:51.500 --> 00:22:53.500
by the total result, we estimate

00:22:53.500 --> 00:22:55.500
the final labor participation coefficient.

00:22:55.500 --> 00:22:57.500
There are very democratic situations

00:22:57.500 --> 00:22:59.500
when this labor participation coefficient

00:22:59.500 --> 00:23:01.500
is roughly assigned by the collective.

00:23:01.500 --> 00:23:03.500
There are absolutely dictatorial situations

00:23:03.500 --> 00:23:05.500
when this labor participation coefficient

00:23:05.500 --> 00:23:07.500
is assigned by the leader.

00:23:07.500 --> 00:23:09.500
Each time it is done in a different way

00:23:09.500 --> 00:23:11.500
depending on which form is more effective.

00:23:11.500 --> 00:23:13.500
These are the traditional

00:23:13.500 --> 00:23:15.500
compensation plans.

00:23:15.500 --> 00:23:17.500
Of course, you have heard these words.

00:23:17.500 --> 00:23:19.500
There is nothing new here.

00:23:19.500 --> 00:23:21.500
And at the same time,

00:23:21.500 --> 00:23:23.500
these plans can be used

00:23:23.500 --> 00:23:25.500
for the assessment

00:23:25.500 --> 00:23:27.500
and payment of labor

00:23:27.500 --> 00:23:29.500
in quite simple cases

00:23:29.500 --> 00:23:31.500
to very complex ones,

00:23:31.500 --> 00:23:33.500
such as the formation

00:23:33.500 --> 00:23:35.500
of the payment system

00:23:35.500 --> 00:23:37.500
of the same project workers.

00:23:37.500 --> 00:23:39.500
Therefore, I highly recommend

00:23:39.500 --> 00:23:41.500
not to forget about these simple

00:23:41.500 --> 00:23:43.500
compensation plans.

00:23:43.500 --> 00:23:45.500
There are many situations

00:23:45.500 --> 00:23:47.500
when the use of these traditional

00:23:47.500 --> 00:23:49.500
and understandable systems

00:23:49.500 --> 00:23:51.500
is not very effective.

00:23:51.500 --> 00:23:53.500
In general, you should not invent

00:23:53.500 --> 00:23:55.500
anything else.

00:23:55.500 --> 00:23:57.500
In other cases,

00:23:57.500 --> 00:23:59.500
it happens that you should.

00:23:59.500 --> 00:24:01.500
We will talk about

00:24:01.500 --> 00:24:03.500
how this will happen.

00:24:03.500 --> 00:24:05.500
One of the factors

00:24:05.500 --> 00:24:07.500
that ensure the attractiveness

00:24:07.500 --> 00:24:09.500
of the employer in the labor market

00:24:09.500 --> 00:24:11.500
is the assurance of the worker

00:24:11.500 --> 00:24:13.500
in the future

00:24:13.500 --> 00:24:15.500
and a certain level of stability.

00:24:15.500 --> 00:24:17.500
Although in most cases

00:24:17.500 --> 00:24:19.500
the payment of labor is somehow

00:24:19.500 --> 00:24:21.500
tied to its results,

00:24:21.500 --> 00:24:23.500
now almost everywhere,

00:24:23.500 --> 00:24:25.500
with a rare exception,

00:24:25.500 --> 00:24:27.500
combined forms of labor payment

00:24:27.500 --> 00:24:29.500
are used, which combine

00:24:29.500 --> 00:24:31.500
temporary payment

00:24:31.500 --> 00:24:33.500
with payment based on results.

00:24:33.500 --> 00:24:35.500
Therefore, it is especially important

00:24:35.500 --> 00:24:37.500
for us to understand how this

00:24:37.500 --> 00:24:39.500
constant component of labor payment

00:24:39.500 --> 00:24:41.500
is formed, according to which

00:24:41.500 --> 00:24:43.500
hourly payment is determined.

00:24:43.500 --> 00:24:45.500
Here we will have to remember

00:24:45.500 --> 00:24:47.500
that the term

00:24:47.500 --> 00:24:49.500
tariff grid

00:24:49.500 --> 00:24:51.500
is a word

00:24:51.500 --> 00:24:53.500
that is often used

00:24:53.500 --> 00:24:55.500
in English.

00:24:55.500 --> 00:24:57.500
In English,

00:24:57.500 --> 00:24:59.500
the word grid

00:24:59.500 --> 00:25:01.500
has several meanings,

00:25:01.500 --> 00:25:03.500
including the category,

00:25:03.500 --> 00:25:05.500
in this case the tariff.

00:25:05.500 --> 00:25:07.500
I prefer the Russian language

00:25:07.500 --> 00:25:09.500
and in the future

00:25:09.500 --> 00:25:11.500
I will use the word

00:25:11.500 --> 00:25:13.500
tariff grid to denote this concept.

00:25:13.500 --> 00:25:15.500
We divide all the employees

00:25:15.500 --> 00:25:17.500
of our enterprise,

00:25:17.500 --> 00:25:19.500
all the positions of our enterprise

00:25:19.500 --> 00:25:21.500
into a number of tariff categories

00:25:21.500 --> 00:25:23.500
and within each category

00:25:23.500 --> 00:25:25.500
we pay the employee

00:25:25.500 --> 00:25:27.500
in time as much as is provided

00:25:27.500 --> 00:25:29.500
in this category.

00:25:29.500 --> 00:25:31.500
Then we multiply by the number

00:25:31.500 --> 00:25:33.500
of working hours.

00:25:33.500 --> 00:25:35.500
What is the advantage of this scheme?

00:25:35.500 --> 00:25:37.500
First, it ensures a certain

00:25:37.500 --> 00:25:39.500
objectivity of labor assessment,

00:25:39.500 --> 00:25:41.500
because these categories of the tariff grid

00:25:41.500 --> 00:25:43.500
are not assigned from the top,

00:25:43.500 --> 00:25:45.500
but are specially developed

00:25:45.500 --> 00:25:47.500
to apply to the level

00:25:47.500 --> 00:25:49.500
of complexity of the work,

00:25:49.500 --> 00:25:51.500
what it requires from the employee

00:25:51.500 --> 00:25:53.500
and how valuable this work

00:25:53.500 --> 00:25:55.500
is for the enterprise.

00:25:55.500 --> 00:25:57.500
The second point,

00:25:57.500 --> 00:25:59.500
if we remember the factors

00:25:59.500 --> 00:26:01.500
of ensuring the efficiency of labor payment,

00:26:01.500 --> 00:26:03.500
is transparency, controllability

00:26:03.500 --> 00:26:05.500
and, what is very important,

00:26:05.500 --> 00:26:07.500
clarity for the employees.

00:26:07.500 --> 00:26:09.500
The employee understands

00:26:09.500 --> 00:26:11.500
what the tariff grid is,

00:26:11.500 --> 00:26:13.500
what the tariff category is,

00:26:13.500 --> 00:26:15.500
and what the conditions are.

00:26:17.500 --> 00:26:19.500
When the tariff grid is built

00:26:19.500 --> 00:26:21.500
and we know

00:26:21.500 --> 00:26:23.500
how many employees

00:26:23.500 --> 00:26:25.500
will receive

00:26:25.500 --> 00:26:27.500
and how much will be paid

00:26:27.500 --> 00:26:29.500
in advance,

00:26:29.500 --> 00:26:31.500
it is very easy to combine

00:26:31.500 --> 00:26:33.500
with the analysis of the enterprise economy

00:26:33.500 --> 00:26:35.500
and we can always understand

00:26:35.500 --> 00:26:37.500
how much of our labor payment

00:26:37.500 --> 00:26:39.500
is paid by the employees

00:26:39.500 --> 00:26:41.500
and we can understand

00:26:41.500 --> 00:26:43.500
how effective it is.

00:26:43.500 --> 00:26:45.500
As I said,

00:26:45.500 --> 00:26:47.500
this system is not only transparent

00:26:47.500 --> 00:26:49.500
for management,

00:26:49.500 --> 00:26:51.500
it is clear for the employees

00:26:51.500 --> 00:26:53.500
and provides them with a certain motivation

00:26:53.500 --> 00:26:55.500
and creates a clear perspective

00:26:55.500 --> 00:26:57.500
of career growth,

00:26:57.500 --> 00:26:59.500
in any case, much better

00:26:59.500 --> 00:27:01.500
than the traditional situation,

00:27:01.500 --> 00:27:03.500
when employees receive their salary

00:27:03.500 --> 00:27:05.500
in envelopes and no one knows

00:27:05.500 --> 00:27:07.500
or suspects anything.

00:27:09.500 --> 00:27:11.500
It seems that this system

00:27:11.500 --> 00:27:13.500
is quite rigid,

00:27:13.500 --> 00:27:15.500
but it is not so.

00:27:15.500 --> 00:27:17.500
It is flexible and adaptive

00:27:17.500 --> 00:27:19.500
because the entire system of grids

00:27:19.500 --> 00:27:21.500
can be moved up or down,

00:27:21.500 --> 00:27:23.500
it changes and it is clear

00:27:23.500 --> 00:27:25.500
how to change it.

00:27:25.500 --> 00:27:27.500
Therefore, it provides

00:27:27.500 --> 00:27:29.500
a high level of adaptability

00:27:29.500 --> 00:27:31.500
and adaptability

00:27:31.500 --> 00:27:33.500
to the conditions of the labor market.

00:27:33.500 --> 00:27:35.500
Today we can have

00:27:35.500 --> 00:27:37.500
one system, one tariff grid,

00:27:37.500 --> 00:27:39.500
and tomorrow we can change it

00:27:39.500 --> 00:27:41.500
according to what is happening

00:27:41.500 --> 00:27:43.500
in the labor market.

00:27:43.500 --> 00:27:45.500
I will say more,

00:27:45.500 --> 00:27:47.500
many enterprises move the tariff grid

00:27:47.500 --> 00:27:49.500
as a compensation for inflation.

00:27:49.500 --> 00:27:51.500
Tariff grid is revised

00:27:51.500 --> 00:27:53.500
every six months or every year

00:27:53.500 --> 00:27:55.500
taking into account inflation.

00:27:55.500 --> 00:27:57.500
Such advantages

00:27:57.500 --> 00:27:59.500
exist in this system.

00:27:59.500 --> 00:28:01.500
I will say right away

00:28:01.500 --> 00:28:03.500
that the implementation of the tariff grid

00:28:03.500 --> 00:28:05.500
where it was not is a big job.

00:28:05.500 --> 00:28:07.500
We will learn how to do it

00:28:07.500 --> 00:28:09.500
in the third part of our course.

