the design of the tariff grid.

00:28:31.500 --> 00:28:33.500
The first one

00:28:33.500 --> 00:28:35.500
is the number of tariff categories.

00:28:35.500 --> 00:28:37.500
How many should there be?

00:28:37.500 --> 00:28:39.500
There are six of them in this picture.

00:28:39.500 --> 00:28:41.500
Maybe eight,

00:28:41.500 --> 00:28:43.500
maybe 16,

00:28:43.500 --> 00:28:45.500
but more than a few dozen

00:28:45.500 --> 00:28:47.500
are rarely seen here.

00:28:47.500 --> 00:28:49.500
The number of tariff categories

00:28:49.500 --> 00:28:51.500
depends on the perspective

00:28:51.500 --> 00:28:53.500
we want to create for our workers,

00:28:53.500 --> 00:28:55.500
how high the ladder

00:28:55.500 --> 00:28:57.500
they can climb

00:28:57.500 --> 00:28:59.500
and how many positions

00:28:59.500 --> 00:29:01.500
they can get.

00:29:01.500 --> 00:29:03.500
If the organization is large

00:29:03.500 --> 00:29:05.500
and there are many different people

00:29:05.500 --> 00:29:07.500
in different positions,

00:29:07.500 --> 00:29:09.500
then the tariff grid

00:29:09.500 --> 00:29:11.500
will probably have

00:29:11.500 --> 00:29:13.500
more categories.

00:29:13.500 --> 00:29:15.500
If it is not so,

00:29:15.500 --> 00:29:17.500
if the number of workers

00:29:17.500 --> 00:29:19.500
is small

00:29:19.500 --> 00:29:21.500
and the number of functions

00:29:21.500 --> 00:29:23.500
and positions is limited,

00:29:23.500 --> 00:29:25.500
then the tariff grid

00:29:25.500 --> 00:29:27.500
will probably be useless.

00:29:29.500 --> 00:29:31.500
The second question

00:29:31.500 --> 00:29:33.500
is about the variables

00:29:33.500 --> 00:29:35.500
such as the minimum wage

00:29:35.500 --> 00:29:37.500
and the maximum wage.

00:29:37.500 --> 00:29:39.500
The minimum wage

00:29:39.500 --> 00:29:41.500
corresponds to the lowest

00:29:41.500 --> 00:29:43.500
category of the tariff grid,

00:29:43.500 --> 00:29:45.500
and the maximum

00:29:45.500 --> 00:29:47.500
corresponds to the highest

00:29:47.500 --> 00:29:49.500
category of the tariff grid.

00:29:51.500 --> 00:29:53.500
What else is important to us?

00:29:53.500 --> 00:29:55.500
The width of the tariff category.

00:29:57.500 --> 00:29:59.500
How much does it fit?

00:30:01.500 --> 00:30:03.500
How wide is this range?

00:30:03.500 --> 00:30:05.500
Where does the tariff category

00:30:05.500 --> 00:30:07.500
end and where does it begin?

00:30:07.500 --> 00:30:09.500
It would seem easy to calculate

00:30:09.500 --> 00:30:11.500
if we know the minimum wage

00:30:11.500 --> 00:30:13.500
and the maximum wage.

00:30:13.500 --> 00:30:15.500
We simply subtract the minimum

00:30:15.500 --> 00:30:17.500
from the maximum,

00:30:17.500 --> 00:30:19.500
divide by the number of grades

00:30:19.500 --> 00:30:21.500
and get the width.

00:30:21.500 --> 00:30:23.500
The width of the tariff category

00:30:23.500 --> 00:30:25.500
shows a noticeable difference

00:30:25.500 --> 00:30:27.500
in the increase in the wage.

00:30:27.500 --> 00:30:29.500
This means that the tariff categories

00:30:29.500 --> 00:30:31.500
do not necessarily have

00:30:31.500 --> 00:30:33.500
the same width.

00:30:33.500 --> 00:30:35.500
In most cases,

00:30:35.500 --> 00:30:37.500
the low tariff categories

00:30:37.500 --> 00:30:39.500
will be smaller than the high

00:30:39.500 --> 00:30:41.500
tariff categories,

00:30:41.500 --> 00:30:43.500
simply because for workers

00:30:43.500 --> 00:30:45.500
at high wages

00:30:45.500 --> 00:30:47.500
the percentage ratio requires

00:30:47.500 --> 00:30:49.500
a greater increase

00:30:49.500 --> 00:30:51.500
in the wage.

00:30:51.500 --> 00:30:53.500
This is a very important point,

00:30:53.500 --> 00:30:55.500
because in some cases

00:30:55.500 --> 00:30:57.500
the tariff categories

00:30:57.500 --> 00:30:59.500
do not intersect,

00:30:59.500 --> 00:31:01.500
which means that

00:31:01.500 --> 00:31:03.500
the higher the tariff category

00:31:03.500 --> 00:31:05.500
begins where the lower

00:31:05.500 --> 00:31:07.500
ends.

00:31:07.500 --> 00:31:09.500
The jump from one category to another

00:31:09.500 --> 00:31:11.500
automatically means an increase

00:31:11.500 --> 00:31:13.500
in the wage.

00:31:13.500 --> 00:31:15.500
If the tariff categories intersect,

00:31:15.500 --> 00:31:17.500
it means that a person

00:31:17.500 --> 00:31:19.500
in the lower category

00:31:19.500 --> 00:31:21.500
can earn even more

00:31:21.500 --> 00:31:23.500
than a person in the higher category.

00:31:23.500 --> 00:31:25.500
Why do these intersections occur?

00:31:25.500 --> 00:31:27.500
These intersections are a very

00:31:27.500 --> 00:31:29.500
delicate management tool

00:31:29.500 --> 00:31:31.500
that provides us

00:31:31.500 --> 00:31:33.500
with a moral factor.

00:31:33.500 --> 00:31:35.500
In some cases,

00:31:35.500 --> 00:31:37.500
it turns out that

00:31:37.500 --> 00:31:39.500
the workers who have been

00:31:39.500 --> 00:31:41.500
working for us for a long time

00:31:41.500 --> 00:31:43.500
and who are attached to us

00:31:43.500 --> 00:31:45.500
are not able to

00:31:45.500 --> 00:31:47.500
work for us anymore.

00:31:47.500 --> 00:31:49.500
They earn a certain level,

00:31:49.500 --> 00:31:51.500
but this level

00:31:51.500 --> 00:31:53.500
does not correspond to the level

00:31:53.500 --> 00:31:55.500
that new workers require.

00:31:55.500 --> 00:31:57.500
We have to hire new workers

00:31:57.500 --> 00:31:59.500
at a higher wage

00:31:59.500 --> 00:32:01.500
than the old ones.

00:32:01.500 --> 00:32:03.500
Of course, this is unfair

00:32:03.500 --> 00:32:05.500
on the one hand,

00:32:05.500 --> 00:32:07.500
but on the other hand,

00:32:07.500 --> 00:32:09.500
it is simply unfair.

00:32:09.500 --> 00:32:11.500
And where do you go from the third side?

00:32:11.500 --> 00:32:13.500
The labor market is changing.

00:32:13.500 --> 00:32:15.500
The labor market allows us

00:32:15.500 --> 00:32:17.500
to manipulate the wage levels

00:32:17.500 --> 00:32:19.500
so that the worker,

00:32:19.500 --> 00:32:21.500
being at the fifth level,

00:32:21.500 --> 00:32:23.500
earns more than at the sixth.

00:32:23.500 --> 00:32:25.500
Thus, the necessary degree

00:32:25.500 --> 00:32:27.500
of justice is observed.

00:32:27.500 --> 00:32:29.500
This situation motivates

00:32:29.500 --> 00:32:31.500
workers more

00:32:31.500 --> 00:32:33.500
and does not encourage them

00:32:33.500 --> 00:32:35.500
to take offense

00:32:35.500 --> 00:32:37.500
and leave our enterprise.

00:32:37.500 --> 00:32:39.500
As we can see,

00:32:39.500 --> 00:32:41.500
it would seem that

00:32:41.500 --> 00:32:43.500
the labor market is changing,

00:32:43.500 --> 00:32:45.500
but on the other hand,

00:32:45.500 --> 00:32:47.500
there are many variables.

00:32:47.500 --> 00:32:49.500
When constructing a tariff grid,

00:32:49.500 --> 00:32:51.500
all these variables,

00:32:51.500 --> 00:32:53.500
both minimum and maximum wage,

00:32:53.500 --> 00:32:55.500
number of shifts, median,

00:32:55.500 --> 00:32:57.500
must be taken into account.

00:32:57.500 --> 00:32:59.500
The range for creativity

00:32:59.500 --> 00:33:01.500
is very wide.

00:33:01.500 --> 00:33:03.500
There is a point of view

00:33:03.500 --> 00:33:05.500
that the enterprise

00:33:05.500 --> 00:33:07.500
should be permeated

00:33:07.500 --> 00:33:09.500
by the tariff grid from bottom to top.

00:33:09.500 --> 00:33:11.500
The enterprise should take into account

00:33:11.500 --> 00:33:13.500
all the workers,

00:33:13.500 --> 00:33:15.500
where the lowest-class cleaner

00:33:15.500 --> 00:33:17.500
is at the bottom,

00:33:17.500 --> 00:33:19.500
and the director is at the top.

00:33:19.500 --> 00:33:21.500
I do not think this is right

00:33:21.500 --> 00:33:23.500
because a number of enterprises

00:33:23.500 --> 00:33:25.500
work as multifaceted enterprises.

00:33:25.500 --> 00:33:27.500
It is difficult to build

00:33:27.500 --> 00:33:29.500
a single tariff grid for the holding

00:33:29.500 --> 00:33:31.500
where several factories,

00:33:31.500 --> 00:33:33.500
logistics system,

00:33:33.500 --> 00:33:35.500
trading house,

00:33:35.500 --> 00:33:37.500
managing company,

00:33:37.500 --> 00:33:39.500
are all working together.

00:33:39.500 --> 00:33:41.500
Should it be built?

00:33:41.500 --> 00:33:43.500
I think it should not.

00:33:43.500 --> 00:33:45.500
It is necessary in cases

00:33:45.500 --> 00:33:47.500
when there are many workers,

00:33:47.500 --> 00:33:49.500
when the range of positions

00:33:49.500 --> 00:33:51.500
is wide enough,

00:33:51.500 --> 00:33:53.500
and it is necessary to sort it out

00:33:53.500 --> 00:33:55.500
and figure out who and how much

00:33:55.500 --> 00:33:57.500
we are going to pay.

00:33:57.500 --> 00:33:59.500
If the range is not so wide

00:33:59.500 --> 00:34:01.500
and the number of workers is not so large,

00:34:01.500 --> 00:34:03.500
we can limit ourselves

00:34:03.500 --> 00:34:05.500
to more primitive labor payment systems,

00:34:05.500 --> 00:34:07.500
without having to go through

00:34:07.500 --> 00:34:09.500
such a complex project

00:34:09.500 --> 00:34:11.500
as creating and introducing

00:34:11.500 --> 00:34:13.500
a tariff grid.

00:34:13.500 --> 00:34:15.500
Let's look at the next table.

00:34:15.500 --> 00:34:17.500
Here is a so-called

00:34:17.500 --> 00:34:19.500
matrix of grades

00:34:19.500 --> 00:34:21.500
for a tariff grid

00:34:21.500 --> 00:34:23.500
with 8 categories.

00:34:23.500 --> 00:34:25.500
Here is another

00:34:25.500 --> 00:34:27.500
big advantage of a tariff grid,

00:34:27.500 --> 00:34:29.500
namely the ability

00:34:29.500 --> 00:34:31.500
to compare the results of labor,

00:34:31.500 --> 00:34:33.500
the value of the enterprise

00:34:33.500 --> 00:34:35.500
and the level of labor payment

00:34:35.500 --> 00:34:37.500
of representatives

00:34:37.500 --> 00:34:39.500
of various departments

00:34:39.500 --> 00:34:41.500
who perform different work.

00:34:41.500 --> 00:34:43.500
As we can see from this grid,

00:34:43.500 --> 00:34:45.500
let's say, the fourth category.

00:34:45.500 --> 00:34:47.500
In the sales department

00:34:47.500 --> 00:34:49.500
we will have a manager

00:34:49.500 --> 00:34:51.500
of sales,

00:34:51.500 --> 00:34:53.500
in HR department

00:34:53.500 --> 00:34:55.500
a manager of selection of personnel,

00:34:55.500 --> 00:34:57.500
in the finance department

00:34:57.500 --> 00:34:59.500
an accountant.

00:34:59.500 --> 00:35:01.500
That is, there is an order

00:35:01.500 --> 00:35:03.500
and we can look at the organization

00:35:03.500 --> 00:35:05.500
as a whole,

00:35:05.500 --> 00:35:07.500
determine where we may have

00:35:07.500 --> 00:35:09.500
shortcomings.

00:35:09.500 --> 00:35:11.500
In those cases,

00:35:11.500 --> 00:35:13.500
when we observe sharp changes

00:35:13.500 --> 00:35:15.500
in the labor market of a structural nature,

00:35:15.500 --> 00:35:17.500
that is, not general,

00:35:17.500 --> 00:35:19.500
but in relation to individual specializations,

00:35:19.500 --> 00:35:21.500
education, profiles of specialists,

00:35:21.500 --> 00:35:23.500
and there is a deficit

00:35:23.500 --> 00:35:25.500
in the labor market,

00:35:25.500 --> 00:35:27.500
we can move the tariff grid

00:35:27.500 --> 00:35:29.500
in relation to those departments

00:35:29.500 --> 00:35:31.500
where such specialists work.

00:35:31.500 --> 00:35:33.500
Let's say,

00:35:33.500 --> 00:35:35.500
if there are necessary engineers

00:35:35.500 --> 00:35:37.500
at our enterprise,

00:35:37.500 --> 00:35:39.500
and the number of such engineers

00:35:39.500 --> 00:35:41.500
in the labor market is very limited,

00:35:41.500 --> 00:35:43.500
in this case we can move

00:35:43.500 --> 00:35:45.500
and change some of the grids

00:35:45.500 --> 00:35:47.500
so that our offer

00:35:47.500 --> 00:35:49.500
becomes more attractive for these workers.

00:35:49.500 --> 00:35:51.500
So, colleagues,

00:35:51.500 --> 00:35:53.500
we have finished with the summary

00:35:53.500 --> 00:35:55.500
of the permanent part of the labor payment

00:35:55.500 --> 00:35:57.500
and we will move on to the variable,

00:35:57.500 --> 00:35:59.500
that is, the premium part.

00:35:59.500 --> 00:36:01.500
In order to summarize the premium part,

00:36:01.500 --> 00:36:03.500
there are many ways,

00:36:03.500 --> 00:36:05.500
coefficients,

00:36:05.500 --> 00:36:07.500
regulations,

00:36:07.500 --> 00:36:09.500
and we will definitely address this

00:36:09.500 --> 00:36:11.500
in the third part of our course.

00:36:11.500 --> 00:36:13.500
But now I would like to talk

00:36:13.500 --> 00:36:15.500
a little about the now widespread

00:36:15.500 --> 00:36:17.500
and very good,

00:36:17.500 --> 00:36:19.500
effective,

00:36:19.500 --> 00:36:21.500
working, clear and transparent system,

00:36:21.500 --> 00:36:23.500
which is called

00:36:23.500 --> 00:36:25.500
the system of key indicators

00:36:25.500 --> 00:36:27.500
or in English

00:36:27.500 --> 00:36:29.500
the key productivity indicators.

00:36:29.500 --> 00:36:31.500
We discussed this system

00:36:31.500 --> 00:36:33.500
in our course on personal assessment,

00:36:33.500 --> 00:36:35.500
now we will return to it again.

00:36:35.500 --> 00:36:37.500
Let me remind you in a nutshell

00:36:37.500 --> 00:36:39.500
what we are talking about.

00:36:39.500 --> 00:36:41.500
We have our organization as a whole,

00:36:41.500 --> 00:36:43.500
a large organization,

00:36:43.500 --> 00:36:45.500
our corporation,

00:36:45.500 --> 00:36:47.500
which has strategic plans.

00:36:47.500 --> 00:36:49.500
In order to understand

00:36:49.500 --> 00:36:51.500
whether we have implemented

00:36:51.500 --> 00:36:53.500
these plans or not,

00:36:53.500 --> 00:36:55.500
we need a set of indicators,

00:36:55.500 --> 00:36:57.500
indicators that will be

00:36:57.500 --> 00:36:59.500
clear and accountable,

00:36:59.500 --> 00:37:01.500
and we can say whether we have implemented

00:37:01.500 --> 00:37:03.500
them or not.

00:37:03.500 --> 00:37:05.500
In order to implement the plans of the corporation

00:37:05.500 --> 00:37:07.500
as a whole,

00:37:07.500 --> 00:37:09.500
each unit must perform

00:37:09.500 --> 00:37:11.500
its functions.

00:37:11.500 --> 00:37:13.500
Based on the company's plans,

00:37:13.500 --> 00:37:15.500
plans of its departments are built,

00:37:15.500 --> 00:37:17.500
for which this system of key indicators

00:37:17.500 --> 00:37:19.500
is also created.

00:37:19.500 --> 00:37:21.500
So, from top to bottom,

00:37:21.500 --> 00:37:23.500
each employee receives

00:37:23.500 --> 00:37:25.500
his own key indicator,

00:37:25.500 --> 00:37:27.500
which he must rely on.

00:37:27.500 --> 00:37:29.500
The payment of bonuses

00:37:29.500 --> 00:37:31.500
depends on how

00:37:31.500 --> 00:37:33.500
these indicators are implemented.

00:37:33.500 --> 00:37:35.500
If 100%, then the employee

00:37:35.500 --> 00:37:37.500
will receive 100% of his bonus,

00:37:37.500 --> 00:37:39.500
if not, then most likely not.

00:37:39.500 --> 00:37:41.500
But if 150%, then maybe

00:37:41.500 --> 00:37:43.500
150% of his bonus.

00:37:43.500 --> 00:37:45.500
The advantage of this system is

00:37:45.500 --> 00:37:47.500
that each employee,

00:37:47.500 --> 00:37:49.500
each unit knows

00:37:49.500 --> 00:37:51.500
how much he will be rewarded,

00:37:51.500 --> 00:37:53.500
even if the unit is functional

00:37:53.500 --> 00:37:55.500
and does not work for the result,

00:37:55.500 --> 00:37:57.500
but for the process.

00:37:57.500 --> 00:37:59.500
It would seem that there should be

00:37:59.500 --> 00:38:01.500
only a temporary form of labor payment.

00:38:01.500 --> 00:38:03.500
This is not the case.

00:38:03.500 --> 00:38:05.500
For each unit, including the accounting,

00:38:05.500 --> 00:38:07.500
the office,

00:38:07.500 --> 00:38:09.500
and all other units

00:38:09.500 --> 00:38:11.500
that work on the process,

00:38:11.500 --> 00:38:13.500
you can enter 2, 3, 4, 5 indicators

00:38:13.500 --> 00:38:15.500
that will clearly determine

00:38:15.500 --> 00:38:17.500
how well they worked.

00:38:17.500 --> 00:38:19.500
The most primitive of them

00:38:19.500 --> 00:38:21.500
is the number of errors.

00:38:21.500 --> 00:38:23.500
Whether they were allowed or not.

00:38:23.500 --> 00:38:25.500
The most important thing here

00:38:25.500 --> 00:38:27.500
is that these indicators

00:38:27.500 --> 00:38:29.500
are clearly and unambiguously written.

00:38:29.500 --> 00:38:31.500
What is the disadvantage of this system?

00:38:31.500 --> 00:38:33.500
It is very difficult to implement.

00:38:33.500 --> 00:38:35.500
When a corporation is large,

00:38:35.500 --> 00:38:37.500
the implementation of such a system

00:38:37.500 --> 00:38:39.500
requires several years,

00:38:39.500 --> 00:38:41.500
huge costs,

00:38:41.500 --> 00:38:43.500
and is not always justified.

00:38:43.500 --> 00:38:45.500
But I want to say that

00:38:45.500 --> 00:38:47.500
if we do not create a system of KPIs

00:38:47.500 --> 00:38:49.500
for the organization as a whole,

00:38:49.500 --> 00:38:51.500
we can introduce such KPIs

00:38:51.500 --> 00:38:53.500
for individual units

00:38:53.500 --> 00:38:55.500
and for individual positions.

00:38:55.500 --> 00:38:57.500
The advantage is that the employee

00:38:57.500 --> 00:38:59.500
will understand what we will

00:38:59.500 --> 00:39:01.500
fund him for,

00:39:01.500 --> 00:39:03.500
and we will understand it very well.

00:39:03.500 --> 00:39:05.500
As for the employees whose tasks

00:39:05.500 --> 00:39:07.500
are functional,

00:39:07.500 --> 00:39:09.500
I want to give the following example,

00:39:09.500 --> 00:39:11.500
which is very indicative

00:39:11.500 --> 00:39:13.500
and historical.

00:39:13.500 --> 00:39:15.500
There is a legend

00:39:15.500 --> 00:39:17.500
that the great and wise king Solomon

00:39:17.500 --> 00:39:19.500
paid his regular doctor

00:39:19.500 --> 00:39:21.500
only when he was healthy.

00:39:21.500 --> 00:39:23.500
But when he was ill,

00:39:23.500 --> 00:39:25.500
he stopped paying.

00:39:25.500 --> 00:39:27.500
Guess what the doctor did

00:39:27.500 --> 00:39:29.500
and what he would do

00:39:29.500 --> 00:39:31.500
if he were paid exactly the opposite.

00:39:31.500 --> 00:39:33.500
In translation into our language,

00:39:33.500 --> 00:39:35.500
this means that for the doctor

00:39:35.500 --> 00:39:37.500
the key indicator of efficiency

00:39:37.500 --> 00:39:39.500
was the health of his employer.

00:39:39.500 --> 00:39:41.500
Accordingly, if the PPI was not carried out,

00:39:41.500 --> 00:39:43.500
the salary was not produced.

00:39:43.500 --> 00:39:45.500
We discussed in detail

00:39:45.500 --> 00:39:47.500
the system of formation

00:39:47.500 --> 00:39:49.500
of the permanent part

00:39:49.500 --> 00:39:51.500
of the salary

00:39:51.500 --> 00:39:53.500
and talked about the formation

00:39:53.500 --> 00:39:55.500
of the premium component.

00:39:55.500 --> 00:39:57.500
Now let's turn to the next component

00:39:57.500 --> 00:39:59.500
of the stimulation system,

00:39:59.500 --> 00:40:01.500
which is called the social package.

00:40:01.500 --> 00:40:09.500
There are many legends,

00:40:09.500 --> 00:40:12.000
many social myths

00:40:12.000 --> 00:40:15.500
and many points of view.

00:40:15.500 --> 00:40:17.500
In particular,

00:40:17.500 --> 00:40:19.500
there is a point of view

00:40:19.500 --> 00:40:21.500
that if we pay a lot to people,

00:40:21.500 --> 00:40:23.500
why should we provide

00:40:23.500 --> 00:40:25.500
some social package?

00:40:25.500 --> 00:40:27.500
This point of view existed

00:40:27.500 --> 00:40:29.500
for a while,

00:40:29.500 --> 00:40:31.500
but then it disappeared.

00:40:31.500 --> 00:40:33.500
It turns out that not everything

00:40:33.500 --> 00:40:35.500
that an organization needs

00:40:35.500 --> 00:40:37.500
is in the state of people

00:40:37.500 --> 00:40:39.500
at the expense of their labor.

00:40:39.500 --> 00:40:41.500
Let's talk about the purpose

00:40:41.500 --> 00:40:43.500
of the social package.

00:40:43.500 --> 00:40:45.500
First, it is a positive

00:40:45.500 --> 00:40:47.500
image of the employer.

00:40:47.500 --> 00:40:49.500
Or, as we said,

00:40:49.500 --> 00:40:51.500
if the organization allows

00:40:51.500 --> 00:40:53.500
the creation of a social package,

00:40:53.500 --> 00:40:55.500
it means that it is stable,

00:40:55.500 --> 00:40:57.500
has certain reserves,

00:40:57.500 --> 00:40:59.500
intends to work further,

00:40:59.500 --> 00:41:01.500
and such an organization

00:41:01.500 --> 00:41:03.500
looks more reliable

00:41:03.500 --> 00:41:05.500
as an employer.

00:41:05.500 --> 00:41:07.500
Second,

00:41:07.500 --> 00:41:09.500
by providing the employees

00:41:09.500 --> 00:41:11.500
with a social package,

00:41:11.500 --> 00:41:13.500
we show respect to them,

00:41:13.500 --> 00:41:15.500
we show that they are

00:41:15.500 --> 00:41:17.500
important to us.

00:41:17.500 --> 00:41:19.500
When a person in an organization

00:41:19.500 --> 00:41:21.500
that has a social package

00:41:21.500 --> 00:41:23.500
comes home and shows

00:41:23.500 --> 00:41:25.500
his family

00:41:25.500 --> 00:41:27.500
what he gets from the organization

00:41:27.500 --> 00:41:29.500
except for the labor payment,

00:41:29.500 --> 00:41:31.500
it usually works on his prestige,

00:41:31.500 --> 00:41:33.500
raises his self-esteem,

00:41:33.500 --> 00:41:35.500
and it is a positive image.

00:41:35.500 --> 00:41:37.500
I want to give you a strange example.

00:41:37.500 --> 00:41:39.500
Now, in most cases,

00:41:39.500 --> 00:41:41.500
managers are hired

00:41:41.500 --> 00:41:43.500
and asked if the social package

00:41:43.500 --> 00:41:45.500
provides for the payment of mobile communication.

00:41:45.500 --> 00:41:47.500
It is quite strange.

00:41:47.500 --> 00:41:49.500
Can people with such a high

00:41:49.500 --> 00:41:51.500
labor payment

00:41:51.500 --> 00:41:53.500
not find money

00:41:53.500 --> 00:41:55.500
for a mobile phone payment?

00:41:55.500 --> 00:41:57.500
In fact, it is a purely moral factor.

00:41:57.500 --> 00:41:59.500
If we pay a person

00:41:59.500 --> 00:42:01.500
for mobile communication,

00:42:01.500 --> 00:42:03.500
we show that he is so important

00:42:03.500 --> 00:42:05.500
that he should be in touch

00:42:05.500 --> 00:42:07.500
and we are ready to pay for it.

00:42:07.500 --> 00:42:09.500
This is a demonstration

00:42:09.500 --> 00:42:11.500
of his importance.

00:42:11.500 --> 00:42:13.500
I think that if we paid

00:42:13.500 --> 00:42:15.500
for the payment of the canteen,

00:42:15.500 --> 00:42:17.500
instead of the high-paid worker,

00:42:17.500 --> 00:42:19.500
they would not be so happy.

00:42:19.500 --> 00:42:21.500
Or the payment of shirts.

00:42:21.500 --> 00:42:23.500
They would not be as happy

00:42:23.500 --> 00:42:25.500
as the payment of a mobile phone.

00:42:25.500 --> 00:42:27.500
The next point

00:42:27.500 --> 00:42:29.500
is the fact

00:42:29.500 --> 00:42:31.500
that it is just

00:42:31.500 --> 00:42:33.500
an increase in the ability

00:42:33.500 --> 00:42:35.500
of our employees.

00:42:35.500 --> 00:42:37.500
The well-known

00:42:37.500 --> 00:42:39.500
components of the social package

00:42:39.500 --> 00:42:41.500
are medical insurance,

00:42:41.500 --> 00:42:43.500
food,

00:42:43.500 --> 00:42:45.500
and payment of travel.

00:42:45.500 --> 00:42:47.500
In some cases,

00:42:47.500 --> 00:42:49.500
it is the delivery of employees

00:42:49.500 --> 00:42:51.500
from the nearest metro station

00:42:51.500 --> 00:42:53.500
to the office.

00:42:53.500 --> 00:42:55.500
We help people in this way,

00:42:55.500 --> 00:42:57.500
but we also solve one problem.

00:42:57.500 --> 00:42:59.500
If a person is sick,

00:42:59.500 --> 00:43:01.500
he needs to be treated.

00:43:01.500 --> 00:43:03.500
If he comes to work

00:43:03.500 --> 00:43:05.500
by public transport,

00:43:05.500 --> 00:43:07.500
he will be nervous,

00:43:07.500 --> 00:43:09.500
he will feel bad,

00:43:09.500 --> 00:43:11.500
he will be late for work.

00:43:11.500 --> 00:43:13.500
And if he comes back,

00:43:13.500 --> 00:43:15.500
he will complain about traffic jams.

00:43:15.500 --> 00:43:17.500
If a person gets to the office

00:43:17.500 --> 00:43:19.500
by car, he will complain

00:43:19.500 --> 00:43:21.500
about traffic jams.

00:43:21.500 --> 00:43:23.500
He will complain about it

00:43:23.500 --> 00:43:25.500
and he will be nervous.

00:43:25.500 --> 00:43:27.500
Therefore, we provide

00:43:27.500 --> 00:43:29.500
a higher level of

00:43:29.500 --> 00:43:31.500
employability for our employees.

00:43:33.500 --> 00:43:35.500
The last point is

00:43:35.500 --> 00:43:37.500
the solution of problems

00:43:37.500 --> 00:43:39.500
that interfere with the work of our employees.

00:43:39.500 --> 00:43:41.500
We could give money to our employees,

00:43:41.500 --> 00:43:43.500
but we will soon see an example

00:43:43.500 --> 00:43:45.500
that shows

00:43:45.500 --> 00:43:47.500
how much more effective

00:43:47.500 --> 00:43:49.500
it is to solve the problems

00:43:49.500 --> 00:43:51.500
of our employees

00:43:51.500 --> 00:43:53.500
than to pay them.

00:43:53.500 --> 00:43:55.500
In such cases,

00:43:55.500 --> 00:43:57.500
problems are not solved

00:43:57.500 --> 00:43:59.500
with money.

00:43:59.500 --> 00:44:01.500
In such cases,

00:44:01.500 --> 00:44:03.500
we should create a social package.

00:44:03.500 --> 00:44:05.500
We are kind and we want

00:44:05.500 --> 00:44:07.500
to do good to our employees.

00:44:07.500 --> 00:44:09.500
It is very pleasant.

00:44:09.500 --> 00:44:11.500
Unfortunately, we are a commercial organization

00:44:11.500 --> 00:44:13.500
and our task is to earn money.

00:44:13.500 --> 00:44:15.500
Therefore, it would be unprofitable

00:44:15.500 --> 00:44:17.500
to invest money in nothing.

00:44:17.500 --> 00:44:19.500
Therefore, when we create

00:44:19.500 --> 00:44:21.500
a social package for our organization,

00:44:21.500 --> 00:44:23.500
we should take into account

00:44:23.500 --> 00:44:25.500
the savings of expenses

00:44:25.500 --> 00:44:27.500
that we would have incurred

00:44:27.500 --> 00:44:29.500
if we did not have a social package.

00:44:29.500 --> 00:44:31.500
Secondly,

00:44:31.500 --> 00:44:33.500
very often organizations

00:44:33.500 --> 00:44:35.500
offer such goods and services

00:44:35.500 --> 00:44:37.500
as a part of the social package

00:44:37.500 --> 00:44:39.500
that the organization

00:44:39.500 --> 00:44:41.500
can solve better

00:44:41.500 --> 00:44:43.500
than the employee.

00:44:43.500 --> 00:44:45.500
I will give you an example.

00:44:45.500 --> 00:44:47.500
The organization offers

00:44:47.500 --> 00:44:49.500
a bank guarantee

00:44:49.500 --> 00:44:51.500
for the payment of loans.

00:44:51.500 --> 00:44:53.500
The organization cannot provide

00:44:53.500 --> 00:44:55.500
such guarantees for itself.

00:44:55.500 --> 00:44:57.500
Or, let's say,

00:44:57.500 --> 00:44:59.500
we sign a collective insurance contract

00:44:59.500 --> 00:45:01.500
with an insurance company

00:45:01.500 --> 00:45:03.500
for the life and medical insurance

00:45:03.500 --> 00:45:05.500
of our employees.

00:45:05.500 --> 00:45:07.500
We would have done it

00:45:07.500 --> 00:45:09.500
if each of our employees

00:45:09.500 --> 00:45:11.500
signed such a contract.

00:45:11.500 --> 00:45:13.500
This would have cost

00:45:13.500 --> 00:45:15.500
much more money.

00:45:15.500 --> 00:45:17.500
We would have bought

00:45:17.500 --> 00:45:19.500
a social insurance service

00:45:19.500 --> 00:45:21.500
for our employees.

00:45:21.500 --> 00:45:23.500
What else can we do?

00:45:23.500 --> 00:45:25.500
The fact is that

00:45:25.500 --> 00:45:27.500
the so-called

00:45:27.500 --> 00:45:29.500
insurance culture of the population

00:45:29.500 --> 00:45:31.500
is not well developed in our country.

00:45:31.500 --> 00:45:33.500
Our people do not like

00:45:33.500 --> 00:45:35.500
to be insured,

00:45:35.500 --> 00:45:37.500
unlike, for example,

00:45:37.500 --> 00:45:39.500
Americans or Europeans

00:45:39.500 --> 00:45:41.500
who know that they should be insured

00:45:41.500 --> 00:45:43.500
because there are risks.

00:45:43.500 --> 00:45:45.500
If our organization

00:45:45.500 --> 00:45:47.500
had a social insurance system

00:45:47.500 --> 00:45:49.500
with a family budget,

00:45:49.500 --> 00:45:51.500
our employees would have forgotten

00:45:51.500 --> 00:45:53.500
about it.

00:45:53.500 --> 00:45:55.500
Our employees are insured.

00:45:55.500 --> 00:45:57.500
They are happy and we are satisfied.

00:45:57.500 --> 00:45:59.500
So, once again,

00:45:59.500 --> 00:46:01.500
there are two important factors.

00:46:01.500 --> 00:46:03.500
First, the cost savings.

00:46:03.500 --> 00:46:05.500
Second, the efficiency of our staff.

00:46:05.500 --> 00:46:07.500
Third, the ability of our organization

00:46:07.500 --> 00:46:09.500
to solve problems better

00:46:09.500 --> 00:46:11.500
than each employee individually.

00:46:11.500 --> 00:46:13.500
This is how you should design

00:46:13.500 --> 00:46:15.500
a social insurance package.

00:46:15.500 --> 00:46:17.500
Let's look at how

00:46:17.500 --> 00:46:19.500
this social insurance package

00:46:19.500 --> 00:46:21.500
can be distributed in the company.

00:46:21.500 --> 00:46:23.500
There are four options.

00:46:23.500 --> 00:46:25.500
Option number one

00:46:25.500 --> 00:46:27.500
is the most common

00:46:27.500 --> 00:46:29.500
and common for all.

00:46:29.500 --> 00:46:31.500
All the employees

00:46:31.500 --> 00:46:33.500
get the same set of goods

00:46:33.500 --> 00:46:35.500
and services

00:46:35.500 --> 00:46:37.500
as part of the social insurance package.

00:46:37.500 --> 00:46:39.500
Is it good?

00:46:39.500 --> 00:46:41.500
Not really.

00:46:41.500 --> 00:46:43.500
On the one hand,

00:46:43.500 --> 00:46:45.500
it shows the unity of all employees

00:46:45.500 --> 00:46:47.500
and the equality of all employees

00:46:47.500 --> 00:46:49.500
from the cleaning lady

00:46:49.500 --> 00:46:51.500
to the deputy general director.

00:46:51.500 --> 00:46:53.500
But is it always justified?

00:46:53.500 --> 00:46:55.500
Probably not.

00:46:55.500 --> 00:46:57.500
That's why there are

00:46:57.500 --> 00:46:59.500
distribution principles.

00:46:59.500 --> 00:47:01.500
One of them is

00:47:01.500 --> 00:47:03.500
hierarchy.

00:47:03.500 --> 00:47:05.500
The more important you are,

00:47:05.500 --> 00:47:07.500
the more you get

00:47:07.500 --> 00:47:09.500
as part of the social insurance package.

00:47:09.500 --> 00:47:11.500
This is not always justified

00:47:11.500 --> 00:47:13.500
because this system

00:47:13.500 --> 00:47:15.500
is not very democratic

00:47:15.500 --> 00:47:17.500
and often makes the employees

00:47:17.500 --> 00:47:19.500
envious of the social insurance package.

00:47:19.500 --> 00:47:21.500
This structure

00:47:21.500 --> 00:47:23.500
is typical

00:47:23.500 --> 00:47:25.500
for old organizations

00:47:25.500 --> 00:47:27.500
where hierarchy and ranks

00:47:27.500 --> 00:47:29.500
are more important than

00:47:29.500 --> 00:47:31.500
the real contribution of employees.

00:47:31.500 --> 00:47:33.500
Another option is

00:47:33.500 --> 00:47:35.500
the tariff grid.

00:47:35.500 --> 00:47:37.500
The higher the tariff grid,

00:47:37.500 --> 00:47:39.500
the more you can get

00:47:39.500 --> 00:47:41.500
as part of the social insurance package.

00:47:41.500 --> 00:47:43.500
This is a more effective

00:47:43.500 --> 00:47:45.500
form of organization

00:47:45.500 --> 00:47:47.500
because it emphasizes

00:47:47.500 --> 00:47:49.500
not only your status

00:47:49.500 --> 00:47:51.500
but also what you bring

00:47:51.500 --> 00:47:53.500
and how much you are valued.

00:47:53.500 --> 00:47:55.500
The last principle is quite new.

00:47:55.500 --> 00:47:57.500
It was born in Japan

00:47:57.500 --> 00:47:59.500
and is called the cafeteria principle.

00:47:59.500 --> 00:48:01.500
What is it?

00:48:01.500 --> 00:48:03.500
Imagine that

00:48:03.500 --> 00:48:05.500
the compensation of lunches

00:48:05.500 --> 00:48:07.500
is paid by the employees

00:48:07.500 --> 00:48:09.500
in the cafeteria,

00:48:09.500 --> 00:48:11.500
the gasoline is paid

00:48:11.500 --> 00:48:13.500
and the children

00:48:13.500 --> 00:48:15.500
are paid

00:48:15.500 --> 00:48:17.500
by the employees

00:48:17.500 --> 00:48:19.500
in the summer.

00:48:19.500 --> 00:48:21.500
Here we have two employees

00:48:21.500 --> 00:48:23.500
who work in the same position.

00:48:23.500 --> 00:48:25.500
They have the same rank

00:48:25.500 --> 00:48:27.500
in the tariff grid

00:48:27.500 --> 00:48:29.500
and the same hierarchy in the company.

00:48:29.500 --> 00:48:31.500
They are equally valuable

00:48:31.500 --> 00:48:33.500
as individuals and carriers

00:48:33.500 --> 00:48:35.500
but only for a moment.

00:48:35.500 --> 00:48:37.500
One of them lives

00:48:37.500 --> 00:48:39.500
on the other side of the city

00:48:39.500 --> 00:48:41.500
and has to drive all the way.

00:48:41.500 --> 00:48:43.500
The other one lives in the next building

00:48:43.500 --> 00:48:45.500
and gets to work in 3 minutes.

00:48:45.500 --> 00:48:47.500
The first one has a stomach ulcer

00:48:47.500 --> 00:48:49.500
so he does not eat at work

00:48:49.500 --> 00:48:51.500
but brings food in a jar.

00:48:51.500 --> 00:48:53.500
The second one

00:48:53.500 --> 00:48:55.500
eats in the cafeteria

00:48:55.500 --> 00:48:57.500
and gets compensated for it.

00:48:57.500 --> 00:48:59.500
One of them is the father

00:48:59.500 --> 00:49:01.500
of three children

00:49:01.500 --> 00:49:03.500
and it is very important

00:49:03.500 --> 00:49:05.500
that these children

00:49:05.500 --> 00:49:07.500
will do their summer work.

00:49:07.500 --> 00:49:09.500
The other one is childless

00:49:09.500 --> 00:49:11.500
and does not need it.

00:49:11.500 --> 00:49:13.500
The package is the same for everyone.

00:49:13.500 --> 00:49:15.500
What should we do?

00:49:15.500 --> 00:49:17.500
The first thing we can do

00:49:17.500 --> 00:49:19.500
is to provide each employee

00:49:19.500 --> 00:49:21.500
with a set of social services

00:49:21.500 --> 00:49:23.500
of his choice.

00:49:23.500 --> 00:49:25.500
But it will be an uncontrollable system

00:49:25.500 --> 00:49:27.500
and we will stop understanding

00:49:27.500 --> 00:49:29.500
who will get what

00:49:29.500 --> 00:49:31.500
and who will not.

00:49:31.500 --> 00:49:33.500
We will not have a system

00:49:33.500 --> 00:49:35.500
that will only distribute

00:49:35.500 --> 00:49:37.500
social services to employees.

00:49:37.500 --> 00:49:39.500
That is why we use the cafeteria

00:49:39.500 --> 00:49:41.500
which is the following.

00:49:41.500 --> 00:49:43.500
Please look at the next slide.

00:49:43.500 --> 00:49:45.500
On the left side of the slide

00:49:45.500 --> 00:49:47.500
we have the options

00:49:47.500 --> 00:49:49.500
that the company can provide

00:49:49.500 --> 00:49:51.500
to the employee in the social package.

00:49:51.500 --> 00:49:53.500
I repeat, these are just examples.

00:49:53.500 --> 00:49:55.500
In fact, the range of these services

00:49:55.500 --> 00:49:57.500
is extremely wide.

00:49:57.500 --> 00:49:59.500
We create several menus

00:49:59.500 --> 00:50:01.500
each of which includes

00:50:01.500 --> 00:50:03.500
four services from this package.

00:50:03.500 --> 00:50:05.500
As an employee, I can choose

00:50:05.500 --> 00:50:07.500
the menu that I like the most.

00:50:07.500 --> 00:50:09.500
If I do not have a family,

00:50:09.500 --> 00:50:11.500
I am young,

00:50:11.500 --> 00:50:13.500
I drive a car,

00:50:13.500 --> 00:50:15.500
I love using my mobile phone,

00:50:15.500 --> 00:50:17.500
I have free time

00:50:17.500 --> 00:50:19.500
and I like to do sports,

00:50:19.500 --> 00:50:21.500
I will choose menu number one

00:50:21.500 --> 00:50:23.500
where I will be paid for gasoline,

00:50:23.500 --> 00:50:25.500
mobile connection, gym,

00:50:25.500 --> 00:50:27.500
and insurance so that

00:50:27.500 --> 00:50:29.500
I do not get hurt.

00:50:29.500 --> 00:50:31.500
If I get hurt, I will get compensation.

00:50:31.500 --> 00:50:33.500
Let us imagine that

00:50:33.500 --> 00:50:35.500
in our company

00:50:35.500 --> 00:50:37.500
a woman works

00:50:37.500 --> 00:50:39.500
on the same rate as me,

00:50:39.500 --> 00:50:41.500
a mother of two children,

00:50:41.500 --> 00:50:43.500
unfortunately she has no husband,

00:50:43.500 --> 00:50:45.500
she does not have enough money,

00:50:45.500 --> 00:50:47.500
so she will probably choose food,

00:50:47.500 --> 00:50:49.500
she will probably choose delivery

00:50:49.500 --> 00:50:51.500
to the office by bus from the subway

00:50:51.500 --> 00:50:53.500
because she does not have a car,

00:50:53.500 --> 00:50:55.500
she will definitely choose

00:50:55.500 --> 00:50:57.500
to pay for her own vacation,

00:50:57.500 --> 00:50:59.500
because it is difficult for her

00:50:59.500 --> 00:51:01.500
to save enough money

00:51:01.500 --> 00:51:03.500
and she will choose

00:51:03.500 --> 00:51:05.500
a vacation for her children

00:51:05.500 --> 00:51:07.500
because the children

00:51:07.500 --> 00:51:09.500
need to be adjusted somewhere in the summer.

00:51:09.500 --> 00:51:11.500
This is how this

00:51:11.500 --> 00:51:13.500
cafeteria principle works.

00:51:13.500 --> 00:51:15.500
It seems to me that today

00:51:15.500 --> 00:51:17.500
it is probably one of the most effective.

00:51:17.500 --> 00:51:19.500
And now, dear colleagues,

00:51:19.500 --> 00:51:21.500
I suggest you consider

00:51:21.500 --> 00:51:23.500
a project that I encountered

00:51:23.500 --> 00:51:25.500
in my work practice,

00:51:25.500 --> 00:51:27.500
which very brightly and beautifully

00:51:27.500 --> 00:51:29.500
demonstrates what a social package is

00:51:29.500 --> 00:51:31.500
and what its mission is,

00:51:31.500 --> 00:51:33.500
what its function is,

00:51:33.500 --> 00:51:35.500
compared to direct payments

00:51:35.500 --> 00:51:37.500
to our employees

00:51:37.500 --> 00:51:39.500
as part of the labor stimulation system.

00:51:41.500 --> 00:51:43.500
In one of the large Russian cities

00:51:43.500 --> 00:51:45.500
there is a reinforced concrete plant,

00:51:45.500 --> 00:51:47.500
a GBI plant,

00:51:47.500 --> 00:51:49.500
a reinforced concrete plant.

00:51:49.500 --> 00:51:51.500
It produces

00:51:51.500 --> 00:51:53.500
construction from concrete,

00:51:53.500 --> 00:51:55.500
which is then used by the same plant

00:51:55.500 --> 00:51:57.500
to build buildings and structures.

00:51:59.500 --> 00:52:01.500
A significant part of the employees

00:52:01.500 --> 00:52:03.500
of this enterprise are women.

00:52:05.500 --> 00:52:07.500
And now imagine

00:52:07.500 --> 00:52:09.500
what happens in May.

00:52:11.500 --> 00:52:13.500
In May, a significant part of the workers

00:52:13.500 --> 00:52:15.500
of our plant

00:52:15.500 --> 00:52:17.500
come there,

00:52:17.500 --> 00:52:19.500
they are put on the table

00:52:19.500 --> 00:52:21.500
with a statement of leaving

00:52:21.500 --> 00:52:23.500
and are removed for three months to the country house.

00:52:23.500 --> 00:52:25.500
Because each of them knows

00:52:25.500 --> 00:52:27.500
what their children will do

00:52:27.500 --> 00:52:29.500
while they are at work.

00:52:29.500 --> 00:52:31.500
And they have holidays.

00:52:31.500 --> 00:52:33.500
They are in the city.

00:52:33.500 --> 00:52:35.500
Who do they go with?

00:52:35.500 --> 00:52:37.500
What do they do there?

00:52:37.500 --> 00:52:39.500
Do they smoke, drink?

00:52:39.500 --> 00:52:41.500
Of course, no mother can stand it.

00:52:41.500 --> 00:52:43.500
And if we also consider

00:52:43.500 --> 00:52:45.500
that she grows potatoes, tomatoes, cucumbers,

00:52:45.500 --> 00:52:47.500
it turns out that

00:52:47.500 --> 00:52:49.500
compensation is quite adequate.

00:52:49.500 --> 00:52:51.500
But this is the period

00:52:51.500 --> 00:52:53.500
when the plant is most loaded

00:52:53.500 --> 00:52:55.500
with orders.

00:52:55.500 --> 00:52:57.500
So what do we have?

00:52:57.500 --> 00:52:59.500
In the summer period,

00:52:59.500 --> 00:53:01.500
the maximum load

00:53:01.500 --> 00:53:03.500
and demand of labor resources.

00:53:03.500 --> 00:53:05.500
And in the same period,

00:53:05.500 --> 00:53:07.500
a sharp drop in labor resources

00:53:07.500 --> 00:53:09.500
of the employees of the enterprise

00:53:09.500 --> 00:53:11.500
with further return or not.

00:53:11.500 --> 00:53:13.500
So what was done?

00:53:13.500 --> 00:53:15.500
A summer camp for children

00:53:15.500 --> 00:53:17.500
was organized at the base of the local foam institute.

00:53:17.500 --> 00:53:19.500
It was called

00:53:19.500 --> 00:53:21.500
Children are our future.

00:53:21.500 --> 00:53:23.500
It provided the entire set,

00:53:23.500 --> 00:53:25.500
including hiking,

00:53:25.500 --> 00:53:27.500
theater performances,

00:53:27.500 --> 00:53:29.500
excursions, sports competitions

00:53:29.500 --> 00:53:31.500
and a mandatory short internship

00:53:31.500 --> 00:53:33.500
at the enterprise with paid money

00:53:33.500 --> 00:53:35.500
for this internship.

00:53:35.500 --> 00:53:37.500
This meant, look how your parents work.

00:53:37.500 --> 00:53:39.500
What happened as a result?

00:53:39.500 --> 00:53:41.500
The current staff

00:53:41.500 --> 00:53:43.500
at this plant

00:53:43.500 --> 00:53:45.500
became negative.

00:53:45.500 --> 00:53:47.500
This means that no one wanted to leave.

00:53:47.500 --> 00:53:49.500
The gate was built in the interest of those who wanted to work there.

00:53:49.500 --> 00:53:51.500
That is, the problem was completely solved.

00:53:51.500 --> 00:53:53.500
The enterprise was booming

00:53:53.500 --> 00:53:55.500
throughout the region,

00:53:55.500 --> 00:53:57.500
became well-known,

00:53:57.500 --> 00:53:59.500
the mayor came, shook hands,

00:53:59.500 --> 00:54:01.500
television came.

00:54:01.500 --> 00:54:03.500
In short, it worked very well

00:54:03.500 --> 00:54:05.500
for PR and advertising of this enterprise.

00:54:05.500 --> 00:54:07.500
And if we count what it cost?

00:54:07.500 --> 00:54:09.500
I will not give you a lot of numbers,

00:54:09.500 --> 00:54:11.500
I will tell you only one thing.

00:54:11.500 --> 00:54:13.500
The amount that was spent on this venture

00:54:13.500 --> 00:54:15.500
was absolutely adequate

00:54:15.500 --> 00:54:17.500
to increase the salary

00:54:17.500 --> 00:54:19.500
of each employee

00:54:19.500 --> 00:54:21.500
at the enterprise

00:54:21.500 --> 00:54:23.500
by 50 rubles.

00:54:23.500 --> 00:54:25.500
Now tell me,

00:54:25.500 --> 00:54:27.500
what do you think would happen

00:54:27.500 --> 00:54:29.500
if we simply increased

00:54:29.500 --> 00:54:31.500
the salary of each employee by 50 rubles?

00:54:31.500 --> 00:54:33.500
How would this affect their behavior?

00:54:33.500 --> 00:54:35.500
Would the employees leave

00:54:35.500 --> 00:54:37.500
the enterprise in the summer?

00:54:37.500 --> 00:54:39.500
I'm afraid that they would not be able to survive

00:54:39.500 --> 00:54:41.500
150 rubles.

00:54:41.500 --> 00:54:43.500
And their problem was solved.

00:54:43.500 --> 00:54:45.500
This is what a social package is.

00:54:45.500 --> 00:54:47.500
We can save money

00:54:47.500 --> 00:54:49.500
to help our employees

00:54:49.500 --> 00:54:51.500
solve their problems.

00:54:51.500 --> 00:54:53.500
We have finished the second part of our lesson,

00:54:53.500 --> 00:54:55.500
which was dedicated to the tools

00:54:55.500 --> 00:54:57.500
for stimulating labor.

00:54:57.500 --> 00:54:59.500
In the third part,

00:54:59.500 --> 00:55:01.500
we will discuss

00:55:01.500 --> 00:55:03.500
how these tools

00:55:03.500 --> 00:55:05.500
are introduced into the organization,

00:55:05.500 --> 00:55:07.500
what we need to do

00:55:07.500 --> 00:55:09.500
to create a good

00:55:09.500 --> 00:55:11.500
and sustainable

00:55:11.500 --> 00:55:13.500
organization.

00:55:13.500 --> 00:55:15.500
And we will also discuss

00:55:15.500 --> 00:55:17.500
how to create a good

00:55:17.500 --> 00:55:19.500
and sustainable

00:55:19.500 --> 00:55:21.500
organization,

00:55:21.500 --> 00:55:23.500
what we need to do

00:55:23.500 --> 00:55:25.500
to create a clear

00:55:25.500 --> 00:55:27.500
and manageable

00:55:27.500 --> 00:55:29.500
tariff grid,

00:55:29.500 --> 00:55:31.500
and what compensation plans

00:55:31.500 --> 00:55:33.500
we can design

00:55:33.500 --> 00:55:35.500
to meet

00:55:35.500 --> 00:55:37.500
the expectations of our employees

00:55:37.500 --> 00:55:39.500
and solve the problem

00:55:39.500 --> 00:55:41.500
of creating an effective

00:55:41.500 --> 00:55:43.500
labor stimulation system.

00:55:43.500 --> 00:55:45.500
Dear colleagues,

00:55:45.500 --> 00:55:47.500
we already know a lot

00:55:47.500 --> 00:55:49.500
about how to create an effective system.

00:55:49.500 --> 00:55:51.500
We know what tools

00:55:51.500 --> 00:55:53.500
we can use to create such a system.

00:55:53.500 --> 00:55:55.500
Let's now play a little

00:55:55.500 --> 00:55:57.500
in an enterprise that wants

00:55:57.500 --> 00:55:59.500
to introduce

00:55:59.500 --> 00:56:01.500
such a system of labor payment

00:56:01.500 --> 00:56:03.500
and stimulation

00:56:03.500 --> 00:56:05.500
to solve two tasks we know well.

00:56:05.500 --> 00:56:07.500
To make the enterprise good

00:56:07.500 --> 00:56:09.500
and the employees too.

00:56:09.500 --> 00:56:11.500
Let's start with the fact

00:56:11.500 --> 00:56:13.500
that we will divide all our employees

00:56:13.500 --> 00:56:15.500
into five categories.

00:56:15.500 --> 00:56:17.500
We pay the lowest

00:56:17.500 --> 00:56:19.500
to the highest.

00:56:19.500 --> 00:56:21.500
And we assign each category

00:56:21.500 --> 00:56:23.500
a point with a step of 100.

00:56:23.500 --> 00:56:25.500
The lowest category

00:56:25.500 --> 00:56:27.500
will have 100 points,

00:56:27.500 --> 00:56:29.500
the next 200, 300, 400, 500.

00:56:29.500 --> 00:56:31.500
Let's say we know

00:56:31.500 --> 00:56:33.500
how to do it.

00:56:33.500 --> 00:56:35.500
It's not that easy, but let's assume we know.

00:56:35.500 --> 00:56:37.500
And now we will build a curve

00:56:37.500 --> 00:56:39.500
that you see on the slide

00:56:39.500 --> 00:56:41.500
and which,

00:56:41.500 --> 00:56:43.500
according to the principle of noticeable difference,

00:56:43.500 --> 00:56:45.500
should have this shape.

00:56:45.500 --> 00:56:47.500
It's not a straight line,

00:56:47.500 --> 00:56:49.500
it will be a curve.

00:56:49.500 --> 00:56:51.500
The slope will decrease

00:56:51.500 --> 00:56:53.500
as the labor payment volume increases.

00:56:53.500 --> 00:56:55.500
So, the low labor payment category

00:56:55.500 --> 00:56:57.500
will be flat,

00:56:57.500 --> 00:56:59.500
and the high labor payment category

00:56:59.500 --> 00:57:01.500
will be almost straight.

00:57:01.500 --> 00:57:03.500
Almost vertical, sorry.

00:57:03.500 --> 00:57:05.500
Now let's analyze

00:57:05.500 --> 00:57:07.500
the real labor payment

00:57:07.500 --> 00:57:09.500
of our employees.

00:57:09.500 --> 00:57:11.500
Let's say,

00:57:11.500 --> 00:57:13.500
this is the real labor payment

00:57:13.500 --> 00:57:15.500
of our employees

00:57:15.500 --> 00:57:17.500
and let's compare it with this curve.

00:57:17.500 --> 00:57:19.500
The blue dots are the drawings.

00:57:19.500 --> 00:57:21.500
What should we pay attention to?

00:57:21.500 --> 00:57:23.500
In general,

00:57:23.500 --> 00:57:25.500
these points in the curve

00:57:25.500 --> 00:57:27.500
are more or less approximated,

00:57:27.500 --> 00:57:29.500
but in some cases

00:57:29.500 --> 00:57:31.500
they are quite far from it.

00:57:31.500 --> 00:57:33.500
The structure of the labor payments

00:57:33.500 --> 00:57:35.500
in our enterprise

00:57:35.500 --> 00:57:37.500
is quite individual.

00:57:37.500 --> 00:57:39.500
And the distribution,

00:57:39.500 --> 00:57:41.500
the deviation from the theoretical curve

00:57:41.500 --> 00:57:43.500
is quite large.

00:57:43.500 --> 00:57:45.500
As a rule, it happens.

00:57:45.500 --> 00:57:47.500
But our task,

00:57:47.500 --> 00:57:49.500
if we want to make the system manageable,

00:57:49.500 --> 00:57:51.500
if we want to bring it

00:57:51.500 --> 00:57:53.500
to a set of understandable

00:57:53.500 --> 00:57:55.500
and manageable parameters,

00:57:55.500 --> 00:57:57.500
it's not enough for us.

00:57:57.500 --> 00:57:59.500
And we want to bring the system

00:57:59.500 --> 00:58:01.500
to such a curve,

00:58:01.500 --> 00:58:03.500
close to the ideal curve,

00:58:03.500 --> 00:58:05.500
at least in the constant part

00:58:05.500 --> 00:58:07.500
of the labor payment.

00:58:07.500 --> 00:58:09.500
To do this,

00:58:09.500 --> 00:58:11.500
we need to do grading,

00:58:11.500 --> 00:58:13.500
that is, to build a tariff grid,

00:58:13.500 --> 00:58:15.500
that is, to distribute all our employees

00:58:15.500 --> 00:58:17.500
by certain ranks,

00:58:17.500 --> 00:58:19.500
depending on the value

00:58:19.500 --> 00:58:21.500
of the employee and his labor for the enterprise.

00:58:21.500 --> 00:58:23.500
And after that,

00:58:23.500 --> 00:58:25.500
we need to compare,

00:58:25.500 --> 00:58:27.500
assign to each of these levels

00:58:27.500 --> 00:58:29.500
a certain fork of deposits,

00:58:29.500 --> 00:58:31.500
which we talked about.

00:58:31.500 --> 00:58:33.500
And after that,

00:58:33.500 --> 00:58:35.500
we need to finish by attaching

00:58:35.500 --> 00:58:37.500
to the system we built

00:58:37.500 --> 00:58:39.500
an additional stimulation system

00:58:39.500 --> 00:58:41.500
in the form of a social package,

00:58:41.500 --> 00:58:43.500
additional payments, bonuses,

00:58:43.500 --> 00:58:45.500
and so on.

00:58:45.500 --> 00:58:47.500
It would seem that this is a very simple

00:58:47.500 --> 00:58:49.500
three-step task.

00:58:49.500 --> 00:58:51.500
In fact, it will take us a lot of time,

00:58:51.500 --> 00:58:53.500
because in solving each of these steps,

00:58:53.500 --> 00:58:55.500
in completing each of these steps,

00:58:55.500 --> 00:58:57.500
there are quite a few degrees of freedom.

00:58:57.500 --> 00:58:59.500
And we still have to choose

00:58:59.500 --> 00:59:01.500
which way to go,

00:59:01.500 --> 00:59:03.500
because, as we have seen,

00:59:03.500 --> 00:59:05.500
the range of options is quite wide,

00:59:05.500 --> 00:59:07.500
from one case,

00:59:07.500 --> 00:59:09.500
when a person receives only

00:59:09.500 --> 00:59:11.500
a temporary payment and nothing else,

00:59:11.500 --> 00:59:13.500
and this system works poorly,

00:59:13.500 --> 00:59:15.500
to another case,

00:59:15.500 --> 00:59:17.500
when he receives only a percentage

00:59:17.500 --> 00:59:19.500
of the result of the work and nothing else,

00:59:19.500 --> 00:59:21.500
and we see that this is also bad.

00:59:21.500 --> 00:59:23.500
But there are quite a few options

00:59:23.500 --> 00:59:25.500
between them,

00:59:25.500 --> 00:59:27.500
and which one we choose depends

00:59:27.500 --> 00:59:29.500
on a number of factors.

00:59:29.500 --> 00:59:31.500
On our will,

00:59:31.500 --> 00:59:33.500
on the quality of our work,

00:59:33.500 --> 00:59:35.500
on our corporate personnel policy,

00:59:35.500 --> 00:59:37.500
on the market sector in which we work,

00:59:37.500 --> 00:59:39.500
and so on.

00:59:39.500 --> 00:59:41.500
The first thing we need to do

00:59:41.500 --> 00:59:43.500
in order to distribute positions

00:59:43.500 --> 00:59:45.500
in our company

00:59:45.500 --> 00:59:47.500
on a certain grid,

00:59:47.500 --> 00:59:49.500
we need to make a description

00:59:49.500 --> 00:59:51.500
and an assessment of these positions.

00:59:51.500 --> 00:59:53.500
What is included here?

00:59:53.500 --> 00:59:55.500
For each position,

00:59:55.500 --> 00:59:57.500
we must specify the following parameters.

00:59:57.500 --> 00:59:59.500
The first is the name of the position,

00:59:59.500 --> 01:00:01.500
so that we can identify it.

01:00:03.500 --> 01:00:05.500
The second is its purpose.

01:00:05.500 --> 01:00:07.500
Why is it needed in the organization?

01:00:07.500 --> 01:00:09.500
What does a person do

01:00:09.500 --> 01:00:11.500
in this position?

01:00:11.500 --> 01:00:13.500
I must tell you right away

01:00:13.500 --> 01:00:15.500
that the assessment sometimes shows

01:00:15.500 --> 01:00:17.500
that some positions are absolutely unnecessary,

01:00:17.500 --> 01:00:19.500
and in vain they exist.

01:00:19.500 --> 01:00:21.500
The third is the place

01:00:21.500 --> 01:00:23.500
in the organizational structure

01:00:23.500 --> 01:00:25.500
of this position,

01:00:25.500 --> 01:00:27.500
to whom it is subordinate,

01:00:27.500 --> 01:00:29.500
and what role it plays in the organizational diagram.

01:00:29.500 --> 01:00:31.500
This is a very important and useful process of analysis,

01:00:31.500 --> 01:00:33.500
because it may turn out

01:00:33.500 --> 01:00:35.500
that our position is suspended somewhere

01:00:35.500 --> 01:00:37.500
and it is not very clear

01:00:37.500 --> 01:00:39.500
to whom the employee who is on it is subordinate.

01:00:39.500 --> 01:00:41.500
Or maybe it is in the wrong place

01:00:41.500 --> 01:00:43.500
and it will have to be moved

01:00:43.500 --> 01:00:45.500
to improve the efficiency of our enterprise.

01:00:45.500 --> 01:00:47.500
The next thing is

01:00:47.500 --> 01:00:49.500
who and what positions

01:00:49.500 --> 01:00:51.500
are subordinate

01:00:51.500 --> 01:00:53.500
to the positions we are considering.

01:00:53.500 --> 01:00:55.500
I mean direct subordination,

01:00:55.500 --> 01:00:57.500
which is conditioned

01:00:57.500 --> 01:00:59.500
by the organizational structure,

01:00:59.500 --> 01:01:01.500
and functional subordination,

01:01:01.500 --> 01:01:03.500
that is, indirect subordination.

01:01:03.500 --> 01:01:05.500
When an employee in this position

01:01:05.500 --> 01:01:07.500
has the right to manage

01:01:07.500 --> 01:01:09.500
in one way or another

01:01:09.500 --> 01:01:11.500
other people at our enterprise

01:01:11.500 --> 01:01:13.500
who are not subordinate to him.

01:01:13.500 --> 01:01:15.500
For example,

01:01:15.500 --> 01:01:17.500
a sales department employee

01:01:17.500 --> 01:01:19.500
can manage a warehouse worker

01:01:19.500 --> 01:01:21.500
who releases the purchased

01:01:21.500 --> 01:01:23.500
product to the buyer.

01:01:23.500 --> 01:01:25.500
The next thing

01:01:25.500 --> 01:01:27.500
that is extremely important

01:01:27.500 --> 01:01:29.500
is the determination of key functions

01:01:29.500 --> 01:01:31.500
and responsibilities.

01:01:31.500 --> 01:01:33.500
That is, in fact, the duty instruction

01:01:33.500 --> 01:01:35.500
what this person should do at work.

01:01:35.500 --> 01:01:37.500
And there should not be many of these functions.

01:01:37.500 --> 01:01:39.500
They should be clear,

01:01:39.500 --> 01:01:41.500
but at the same time they should be very clear.

01:01:41.500 --> 01:01:43.500
In some cases,

01:01:43.500 --> 01:01:45.500
it turns out that functions

01:01:45.500 --> 01:01:47.500
that no one performs at the enterprise

01:01:47.500 --> 01:01:49.500
are formed,

01:01:49.500 --> 01:01:51.500
they should be performed.

01:01:51.500 --> 01:01:53.500
And this duplication should also be avoided.

01:01:53.500 --> 01:01:55.500
The next thing is the education

01:01:55.500 --> 01:01:57.500
that is required

01:01:57.500 --> 01:01:59.500
to take this position.

01:01:59.500 --> 01:02:01.500
Sometimes this education

01:02:01.500 --> 01:02:03.500
is very high.

01:02:03.500 --> 01:02:05.500
Sometimes we overestimate them.

01:02:05.500 --> 01:02:07.500
There are a number of cases

01:02:07.500 --> 01:02:09.500
when a person without a higher education

01:02:09.500 --> 01:02:11.500
can quite well cope

01:02:11.500 --> 01:02:13.500
with this position,

01:02:13.500 --> 01:02:15.500
and we require that he

01:02:15.500 --> 01:02:17.500
must have completed the higher education.

01:02:17.500 --> 01:02:19.500
And what is very important

01:02:19.500 --> 01:02:21.500
is the improvement of the qualification.

01:02:21.500 --> 01:02:23.500
As I said,

